title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes and then mash them. Combine all of the ingredients together in a mixing bowl and then pour into the unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and bell pepper.
Drain oil; add all dry ingredients, then add tomatoes, water, tomato sauce, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour or until well done.

title: aunt bea's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy. Add lemon juice, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until center is set.

title: sausage breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Line pie shell with Mozzarella cheese. Crumble sausage over cheese. Cover sausage with Cheddar cheese. Beat eggs and milk. Pour over sausage and cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add mashed bananas and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and combine; add vanilla.
Bake in greased loaf pan in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, salt, egg, flour, butter and cinnamon. Pour this mixture into a prepared 6 1/2 x 10-inch rectangular dish or a 10-inch pie pan lined with pastry. Roll out second recipe for pastry and cut in strips and put on top of the pie. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: tropical fruit salad(no fat, low sugar)
directions: Drain fruit salad.
Combine cottage cheese and yogurt.
Layer in glasses or bowl:
cottage cheese mixture, fruit salad and granola.

title: stuffed eggplant and tomatoes(taua)
directions: Prepare stuffing:
Finely chop onion and green pepper and parsley.
Food processor with knife blade works great.
Add salt, pepper, paprika, allspice to ground meat.
Also add tomato paste. Mix with onion, pepper and parsley that has been chopped.
Set aside.
Lay tomato down, seam side down and cut slits about 1/2-inch apart.
Do not go completely through tomato.
Trim eggplant and cut into rounds.
Put in colander and sprinkle with salt.
Let drain for 20 minutes.

title: graham muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add milk and egg and beat well. Add melted Crisco. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Makes 12.

title: mountain candy
directions: Leave cheese out of refrigerator overnight at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together with hands.
Form into roll or press flat into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Grease 1 (9-inch) pie pan or a 10-inch quiche pan. Scatter drained ham in pan. Evenly scatter cheese over ham. Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender. Pour into pan. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian ice cream
directions: Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Add almonds, stirring to coat with butter.
Lightly sprinkle almonds with salt.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes, or until golden.
Cool.
Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl; stir well.
Spoon into 9-inch square pan.
Cover; freeze until firm.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: cherrywinks cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into balls.
Crush 2 1/2 cups corn flakes.
Roll each ball of dough in corn flakes.
Top each cookie with a 1/4 piece of cherry.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cover bottom of large casserole dish with bread cubes.
Layer sausage on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and spices together and pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes the next morning.
Serves 6.

title: okra casserole
directions: In 8 x 8-inch pan, slice a layer of potatoes, then a layer of onion.
Repeat with potatoes.
Slice butter on top to suit yourself.
Cover.
Place in microwave for 9 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Salt and pepper; sprinkle celery seed on top.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
If using frozen shrimp, let it thaw.
Mix together the shrimp, onion, celery and macaroni.
Add enough mayonnaise to please yourself.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and chil 3 to 4 hours.
Serve.
Even better the second day.

title: heavenly dirt(looks and tastes great!)
directions: Pour milk into large bowl, adding pudding mix.
Beat with whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in whipped topping and 1/2 of cookies.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream cheese and margarine. Add flour, salt and pepper. Mix well. Add rice cereal and mix with hands, as dough is very stiff. Roll into walnut-size balls and flatten into cookie with fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield 7 to 9 dozen.

title: meat loaf patties
directions: Mix the ground chuck and eggs together.
Wet the 2 slices of bread in warm water; rinse the bread over the ground chuck so that the bread can fall in the bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients. Mix everything together.
Form a patty in your hand.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook until both sides are brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and pineapple (save juice).
Mix Tang and pudding into juice.
Mix all together.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until soft (don't overcook).
In bowl mix together, ranch dressing, sour cream, bacon bits, green onions and chives and 1/2 bag of cheese until well blended.
Cut potatoes in quarters and place in large casserole dish.
Pour ranch dressing mixture over potatoes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 35 minutes or until cheese has melted and mixture is bubbling up the side of the dish.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with mixture.
Brown in shortening thoroughly.
Add water, potatoes, carrots, onions and celery.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours and add all the rest of ingredients.
If desired, thicken stew by shaking in covered jar 1/2 cup cold water and 2 tablespoons flour until blended.
Stir into stew.
Boil for 1 minute.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, oil, water and eggs together.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut a loaf of Italian, French or rye bread.
Put mix in center and use leftover bread for dipping.
Dip freezes well.

title: chocolate chip cookies(soft)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda and baking powder; stir.
Ad chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Stir (will be quite stiff).
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 20 minutes.

title: easy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley. Serves 8.

title: white frosting for red velvet cake
directions: Mix flour and salt; slowly add milk.
Cook until thick; cool. Beat Crisco and sugar together until fluffy.
Add cooled flour mixture to Crisco mixture; beat well.
Add vanilla; spread on cake.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix both soups and tomatoes, cutting up tomatoes.
Add onion and chili powder along with 1 cup cheese.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with 3/4 cup Doritos.
Mix chicken with soup mixture and pour over Doritos.
Put remaining Doritos and cheese on top.
Cover and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Mix ingredients (except chocolate chips) thoroughly with beater.
Add chocolate chips (can use whole bag).
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can be baked in loaf pan or cupcake tins.

title: green tomato bread
directions: Place green tomatoes in blender; puree then strain to get out all the liquid.
In a large bowl beat together sugar, eggs, green tomatoes, salt, oil, vanilla and almond.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack and remove from pans.
Bread may be frozen for future use if desired.

title: venison stew
directions: Salt and pepper venison cubes; brown lightly in 2 tablespoons butter or oil.
Put celery and onion in crock-pot.
Add browned meat cubes and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 12 hours (high, 4 to 6 hours), stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice or buttered noodles.

title: lemon ginger chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar, lemon peel, lemon juice, ginger and salt; stir well.
Add chicken, grapes and celery.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Can be served in melon halves with toasted almond slivers sprinkled on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil 1 cup berries and water; simmer 2 minutes.
Sieve berry mixture.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Spread 1/4 cup glaze on bottom and sides of baked pie shell.
Mix 5 cups strawberries with remaining glaze.
Pour into greased pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pesto and sundried pasta
directions: Process basil, olive oil, pine nuts and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese in food processor.
Toss with noodles, remaining Parmesan cheese and sundried tomatoes.
Ready to serve.

title: deluxe macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni per package directions.
Rinse and set aside. Combine the next 6 ingredients; add macaroni and stir well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: fri-bake chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Fry onions, green peppers and chicken on both sides for 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pictsweet stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat in oil.
Add soy sauce.
Add Chinese stir-fry (follow directions on package).
Prepare Rice-A-Roni (follow directions on box).
Add rice mix to vegetable mix.
Add water chestnuts.
Add soy sauce as needed.

title: chicken with mushrooms and sour cream
directions: Cut each chicken breast into 1/2-inch strips.
Melt butter in large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and scallions sprinkled with salt.
Cook chicken strips until lightly browned.
Add undiluted mushroom soup, sliced mushrooms with liquid and 1/4 cup water.
Heat to boiling, stirring until smooth.
Reduce heat and add sour cream.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken broccoli soup
directions: Boil water with can of broccoli soup.
Stir in chicken pieces. Add butter.
Let boil.
Add cooked rice.
To make it thicker, lessen butter and water.
Can pour over rice, if desired.
Makes a nice pot of soup.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine the sugar, liqueur, cognac and cherry juice and cherries, if desired.
Just before serving, add remaining ingredients.
This punch is beautiful served in a silver bowl with a fancy ice block floating in it.
This recipe serves 10.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time and blend in.
Combine dry ingredients. Add 1/3 of dry ingredients to liquid mixture; mix thoroughly.
Then add 1/3 milk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Repeat, adding dry ingredients and milk until completely used.
Mash 1/2 cup of blueberries and stir into mixture by hand.
Fold in remaining 2 cup of blueberries until thoroughly mixed.
Grease muffin tin with shortening (even top of pan).
Flour pan.
Add mix to pan. Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test middle of muffin with toothpick to make sure it is completely done.

title: grilled honey burgers
directions: In a bowl, combine honey, cinnamon, paprika, curry powder, ginger and nutmeg. Add beef and mix well. Shape into 8 (3/4-inch) thick patties. Grill, uncovered, over medium heat for 3 minutes on each side; brush with soy sauce. Continue cooking for several minutes until juices run clear, basting and turning several times. During last few minutes, grill pineapple slices until lightly browned, turning once.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with Pam.
Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in dry mixture.
Place on prepared pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until tender and brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball and chill.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix everything but soup and Gravy Master.
Pack on a cookie sheet; let stand overnight in fridge.
Cut into squares.
Coat in flour and fry in a little Crisco until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Cover with the 4 cans of soup that have been diluted with 4 cans of water and enough Kitchen Bouquet to make brown.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Serve with mashed potatoes covered with the gravy mixture.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 3 eggs and butter; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Combine cream cheese with 2 eggs and box of powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: greektown dressing
directions: Combine in cruet and shake vigorously.
Chill before using.

title: shamrock shakes
directions: In a blender, place 1 scoop vanilla ice cream, 1 cup milk and 2 drops of green food coloring.
If desired, add 1/4 teaspoon peppermint flavoring.
Blend until smooth, then pour into cups. Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: rouladen
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: shrimp dip #2
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Thaw artichokes and drain thoroughly.
Chop into small pieces. Add all ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: two cheese salad dressing
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine cheeses, sour cream, mustard and lemon juice.
Beat at medium speed until light.
Stir in vegetables and fold in whipped cream. Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before stirring again and serving.
May be stored in the freezer and thawed before serving.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Let cool and cut into bars.

title: chili cheese soup
directions: This is the quickest, easiest soup to make and it is wonderful, thick and hearty.

title: york sensational brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl with spoon or wire whisk, stir butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; stir until well blended.
Stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Reserve 2 cups batter; set aside.

title: french meat pie
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Remove and set aside.
Brown meat.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients, except pastry.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix all together until well moistened.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: oil salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a quart jar and shake it until the sugar dissolves. Stir well before using.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise and water chestnuts.
Stir in soup mix.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed well.
Chill and serve with wheat crackers.

title: belles waffles
directions: Beat eggs, oil and milk together; add dry ingredients and vanilla.
This batter is better if it sets overnight.
Pour recommended amount in waffle iron and cook according to waffle iron instructions.

title: freezer coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Making 2 round layers. Split layers in half making 4 layers after cooling.
Blend sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Spread all but 1 cup between layers.
Blend remaining cup of sour cream mixture with cool whip. Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal in air tight container and place in freezer.
Leave in freezer for at least 2 days.
Set out 2 hours before cutting.
Refrigerate after cutting.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Mix onions, vinegar, oil, curry and rice.
Marinate about 2 hours ahead.
Add rest when ready to serve.

title: mock cranberry collins
directions: In a tall glass, pour cranberry juice cocktail and lime juice over ice cubes.
Top with club soda.
Stir.
Makes 1 serving.

title: overnight veggies
directions: Combine peas, green beans, corn, onion, celery and pimento in a large bowl.
Combine in saucepan the sugar, vegetable oil, white wine vinegar, salt and black pepper.
Heat until sugar dissolves. Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable hot dish
directions: Cook vegetables until just about done and drain.
In hot dish, mix soup, sour cream, vegetables and water chestnuts.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Add cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Add onions and bake about 2 minutes more at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour teriyaki
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box; set aside.
Brown ground beef in 12-inch skillet; drain.
Mix all ingredients, except rice, in beef.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice; mix well.

title: mississippi sausage cornbread
directions: Brown sausage in medium skillet and heat.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine cornmeal and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Stir well and pour half of batter into a greased 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Arrange sausage on top of batter.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheese.
Spread remaining half of batter over cheese.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes; sprinkle with remaining 3/4 cup cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: shrimp elegante
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails on; devein and butterfly.
Place shrimp in salted boiling water for 30 seconds.
Drain and place in a shallow broiling pan.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add onion, egg and buttermilk; beat well.
Drop balls into deep fryer.
Fry until they float on top of oil.
Drain on a paper towel.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 cup fluted tube pan. In large bowl, blend cake mix, eggs, oil, water, brown sugar and cinnamon until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Fold in shredded carrots, raisins and nuts.
Spoon into tube pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool upright 25 minutes.
Cool completely before serving.

title: easy blueberry pie
directions: Cook thawed blueberries in 1 1/2 cups water for 5 minutes. Add sugar and orange juice; cook for 5 minutes longer.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; mix well.
Add cornstarch mixture to blueberry mixture, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with fresh blueberries.
Serve cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk for 9 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add chips, Marshmallow Whip, vanilla and nuts. Beat until mixed well. Pour into pan. Makes 5 pounds.

title: grandma's grape juice
directions: Clean and scald 4 1/2 gallon canning jars. Put 2 cups clean grapes in each jar. Add 1 cup sugar per jar. Fill with boiling water. Adjust lids. Process in water bath for 30 minutes. Best if not used for at least 3 to 4 months.

title: periogies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll dough in a large circle.
Cut into big squares.
Fill the dough with the potato or cheese filling. Squeeze ends tight and place in boiling water until they float. Rinse in cold water.
Drain well, then pan fry in butter.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Press 2/3 of mixture
into cookie sheet (will cover about 3/4 of pan).
Spread apricot preserves over this.
Put rest of mixture over the top in small pieces.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Prepare chili.
Fry refried beans until pasty.
Layer: Chili on bottom, sour cream, refried beans and Cheddar cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain apricots 1 hour (very dry).
Sprinkle Jell-O over them and stir.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Mix together. Chill.

title: anna's banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and bananas.
Mix well.
Mix flour and baking soda together; add to mixture.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken marbella
directions: Combine these ingredients and marinate overnight. Place chicken and marinade in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle 1 cup white wine and 1 cup brown sugar. Bake 1 hour at 350°, basting frequently. Transfer to serving dish. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: spicy pecan apple salad
directions: Melt butter. Mix salt, cinnamon, cayenne pepper and pecans with butter.
Bake pecan mixture at 350 for 15 min. or until golden brown. Set aside. To prepare dressing mix together sherry wine vinegar, dry mustard, and olive oil.
Set aside. Toss together greens, chopped apple, and feta cheese.
Add pecans and dressing to greens mixture.

title: snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir in crackers.
Stir until well mixed.
Will freeze well.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Combine cake mix, milk, eggs and oil; mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put into layer cake pans and bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until done.
Let cool on rack and then frost.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Let first 5 ingredients chill in refrigerator overnight. Spread on room temperature tortillas.
Roll up and cut.
Hold in place with toothpicks.
Serve with picante sauce or salsa.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, then the banana.
Mix in the Jiffy mix.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350 until done.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cinnamon and sugar; set aside. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in apples, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and stir well.
Add walnuts.
Batter will be very thick. Spoon 1/3 of batter in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Repeat 2 more times, ending with cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour or until center is set.
Yield:
1 large loaf.

title: cheese and sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into walnut size balls. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Whip the Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Whip again and add sugar.
Mix well, spread over pretzels.
Top with pie filling.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts in pieces, place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dilute chicken soup to gravy consistency.
Heat, pour over chicken.
Spoon prepared stuffing over soup.
Dot with butter if desired.
Bake at 400° until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square or oblong baking dish.
(I use Pam.)
Blend ingredients and pour into prepared pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Separate eggs 1 hour before making cake.
Beat egg yolks well. Beat 1/2 cup cold water into the egg yolks.
Add the sugar gradually and beat after each addition.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt (sifted together), gradually folding in each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: chocolate crunch cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Grease cookie sheets.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: granny clara's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Crumble prefried bacon over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: corn saladroswell, new mexico
directions: Combine, toss, cover and chill.
Can be prepared a day in advance.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear up lettuce.
Slice tomato.
Put all in large bowl and toss!
(Left overs are good, but Doritos will get soft.)

title: apple stake cake
directions: Use a box of spice cake mix.
Make according to the directions on box.
Cook apples until tender and add sugar to taste.
Stake with 2 cups dried apples.
A good cake.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Mix coleslaw and onions.
Break up dry noodles from soup mix. Add noodles, almonds and sunflower seeds to coleslaw mix.
(Don't add noodles too far in advance, as noodles will get soggy.)
When ready to serve, add dressing and toss together well.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Mix evaporated milk and sugar with margarine, stirring until it comes to a rolling boil. Boil and stir for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate bits, Marshmallow Fluff, nuts and vanilla and mix until smooth with wooden spoon.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, score.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: beulah's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well and set aside.
Combine Karo, sugar and margarine in deep saucepan.
Cook over medium to medium-high until rolling boil.
Take off heat.
Add vanilla.
Add this to beaten eggs.
Add pecans.
Divide into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until firm (approximately 1 hour).

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour together.
Add milk and eggs to it.
Put on stove.
Let it come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Wait until ready to put in pie shell to add 1 tablespoon butternut vanilla flavoring.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Have oven preheated to 450°.

title: strawberry pop cake #2(sugar-free)
directions: Bake the cake mix in an oblong 9 x 13 pan.
When done, punch full of holes and pour the strawberry pop over this while cake is hot.
Mix up the Jell-O with 1 cup of water and also pour over cake.
Put in the refrigerator to cool.
When cool, ice.

title: sangria (spanish wine punch)
directions: Combine juices, wine, rum and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Slice orange thinly.
Cut slices in half.
Add orange slices, maraschino cherries and cinnamon stick to wine mixture.
Let stand one hour.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Pour into water goblets one-quarter filled with cracked ice or small ice cubes.
Yields 12 to 24 servings.

title: sausage squares
directions: Combine biscuit mix with milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise. Spread in oblong baking pan (do not grease).
Mixture will be very thin, but spread evenly into the corners.
Meanwhile, brown sausage in skillet, stirring often to break up.
Add onion and continue stirring and cooking until meat is brown and onion crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Spread sausage mixture evenly over biscuit dough.
In medium mixing bowl stir together the egg, grated cheese and remaining mayonnaise and green chilies.
Spread on top of sausage and press down lightly.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
This can be baked ahead.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple, milk, lemon juice and nuts.
Divide mixture between 2 pie shells.
Chill.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by directions on box.
Place 1/3 batter in a greased and floured tube pan.
Place 1/2 of dry frosting mix on cake batter.
Place 1/3 of chocolate chips and 1/3 of pecans over this.
Repeat layers.
Then place last 1/3 of batter on top. Sprinkle with remainder of chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
May glaze or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: sweet sour meatballs
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese.
Mix all together and roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll out and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chess pie(old southern)
directions: Beat all the above well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crackers and melted margarine) and put in a casserole dish. Put finely crushed crackers on top and pour melted butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Blend until crumbly.
Press 2 3/4 cups of mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients except apples to the rest of mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in apples. Spoon over base.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes until toothpick tests clean.

title: banana split cake
directions: Have oleo at room temperature.
Pat graham cracker crumbs and one stick oleo into a long Pyrex dish.
Mix confectioners sugar, one stick oleo, cream cheese and eggs until melted.
(Note:
Use double boiler and beat eggs before adding to mix.)

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil.
Combine sauteed onion and celery with bread crumbs, egg and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll mixture in chicken breasts and secure with toothpicks.
Mix soup and milk until diluted to a pouring consistency and cover chicken breasts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter-brickle cake
directions: Blend together for 3 minutes. Spread half the batter in 9 x 13 cake pan. Sprinkle half the sugar mixture, then the rest of the batter and sugar mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy cheesy vegetable delight
directions: Put 1/2 of precooked, drained vegetables in a layer on the bottom of a large casserole.
Put 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of crackers in next layer.
Then layer the rest of vegetables.
On top, spread rest of cheese, crackers and melted butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: creamy horseradish
directions: Whip cream and fold in rest of ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: peachy rice
directions: Boil rice in salt water until soft.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Beat well eggs in a bowl.
Add cream, milk and sugar. Beat until well blended.
Add rice and mix.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan and pour mixture into pan.
Drain peaches well.
Lay on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken breast and white bean salad
directions: Season chicken with thyme, salt and pepper.
In large nonstick skillet, over medium-high heat, add 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken and brown for 2 minutes, reduce heat to medium-low and cook for 2 minutes per side.
Remove and reserve.
Add zucchini, onion and dried tomatoes.
Saute briefly; add beans and toss until heated thoroughly.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix and add milk to fill one-gallon freezer.
Freeze.
This is very rich and creamy.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Prebake pie crusts at 400° until just beginning to turn golden.
Cool.
In large bowl, combine both sugars and flour.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine eggs, milk and vanilla and set aside.

title: taco mac salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Brown meat and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and mix well.
Cool.
In a large bowl, mix macaroni, green pepper, onion, cheese, tomatoes, lettuce and seasonings. Chill.
Just before serving, stir in seasoned ground beef, French dressing and corn chips.
Toss lightly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: veggie salad
directions: Chop vegetables into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook potatoes and zucchini in water until just tender.
Combine with potatoes and add raw celery.
While hot, toss with cilantro, parsley and cider vinegar.
Combine oil, garlic, white vinegar, salt and pepper. Toss with salad and chill.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in saucepan and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Let cool (do not drain), cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla; combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Drop by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: beverly's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon. Pour into baking dish. Top with sliced bacon. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Drain 1 can of pork and beans.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for an hour or so.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press can of crescent rolls onto pizza pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Spread with cream cheese. Top with salsa.
Sprinkle on diced, grated veggies.
Top with shredded cheese.
Chill 2
hours. Slice and serve.

title: black-eyed peas and ham hock
directions: Cook ham hock until done, reserving 3 cups liquid.
Add black-eyed peas to boiling liquid and ham hock. Cook slowly until peas are soft.
Season to taste.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange blueberries in an ungreased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Mix the sugar, flour, oats, margarine and salt; sprinkle on top.
Bake until topping is light brown or 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Wash chicken.
While still wet, coat with bread crumbs.
Fry chicken in hot oil until nicely browned.
Pour spaghetti sauce into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place browned chicken on sauce.
Top each breast with a slice of Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese to taste. Place in a 350° oven and bake approximately 30 minutes, until cheese bubbles.

title: wanda's little debbie bars
directions: Make 36 or more Ritz peanut butter cracker sandwiches.
Melt the almond bark in microwave.
Dip each sandwich in the melted almond bark.
Place each dipped sandwich on wax paper or aluminum foil to dry.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onions in fat until brown.
Add other ingredients.
Put in uncovered dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Make cream sauce of first 3 ingredients.
Add cayenne pepper and cheese; set aside.
Mix cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted butter; set aside.
In buttered casserole, add in layers the asparagus, peas, half of cracker crumbs and mushrooms.
Top with sauce, followed by other half of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: smoked sausage and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cook rice and keep warm.
Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly. Mix in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Stir over rice and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: raisin-spice drops
directions: Sift flour or flour mixture with spices.
In large bowl at medium speed, beat shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: microwave vanilla cream pie
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add milk, mixing well.
Cook with microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes or until thick, stirring every minute.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Gradually add some of the hot mixture to egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Add combine egg mixture to hot mixture and mix well.
Cook with microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes until thick, stirring every 30 seconds.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour hot filling into baked pie shell.
Cool. Top with whipped cream or meringue.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hilda's party salad(this is one of my special fruit salads.)
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve cherry gelatin in 4 cups boiling water. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: layer cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together.
Add sugar.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Cream together.
Add flavoring.
Pour into 4 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken and broccoli
directions: Place chicken breasts in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, cover each breast with broccoli florets.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 375° or until broccoli is tender.
Remove from oven, cover broccoli with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven, uncovered, until cheese is melted.

title: moms sloppy joes
directions: Boil one cup of water and 3/4 cup ketchup.
Add one to two tablespoons chili powder.
Boil for 7 minutes.
Add the ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and mustard.
Cook for 20 minutes. Drain off grease.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients and onion.
Add buttermilk; stir just until corn meal mixture is moistened.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls into deep, hot fat (375°).

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix fat and sugar in large bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and bananas together.
Add salt, soda, buttermilk, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Marinate chicken pieces 2 hours or overnight in Ziploc bag.
Shake drained chicken in cornstarch (only need a small amount to just dust the chicken).
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Combine marinade, pineapple and juice, juice of lemon and orange juice. Pour over chicken and continue baking 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Will thicken as baking.
Overcooking will result in less liquid.
I add extra orange juice.

title: coconut cake topping
directions: Bake any white cake mix.
When done, have already mixed the remaining ingredients.
Pour over warm cake and brown under broiler.
Watch closely.
Serve warm.

title: creamy parmesan cheese sauce
directions: Microwave cream cheese, milk and Parmesan cheese in 1 quart measure.
Microwave on Medium (50%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until sauce is smooth, stirring every 2 minutes.
Stir in seasonings. Toss with hot cooked pasta.
Can add diced turkey or crab.

title: jello punch
directions: Heat enough water to dissolve sugar and jello (whichever flavor
you
like,	I
use strawberry).
Then add pineapple juice and
lemon	juice;	finish	filling
gallon with water. Shake well; chill.

title: layered delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, nuts and melted butter.
Spread in oblong pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Drain.
Add margarine. Add salt and sugar to taste.
Mash up cornbread and add to squash mixture until right consistency.
Bake.

title: joe's fish
directions: Place catfish fillets in casserole-type dish and pour lemon juice over fish.
Leave for one hour.
Place fillets on charcoal grill and baste with melted margarine.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes (depending on grill temperature).
After turning fillets, baste again and cook for another 15 to 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix pudding, flour, baking powder and salt. Add melted butter, milk and egg.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan. Cover with drained peaches.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 cup peach juice together.
Pour over peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: avocado-orange salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except the cinnamon and sugar.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll balls into mixture.
Bake 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet until lightly brown, but soft.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: two coconut pies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add milk and vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into cream mixture.
Add coconut.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili con carne (beef, lamb, pork or veal)(no.  k-114)
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Cover with cold water; soak 8 hours. Cover and heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender, but not split or mushy.
Drain.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease baking dish with margarine.
Add water, rice and mushrooms.
Sprinkle onion soup on top; dot with margarine. Arrange chicken pieces on top, cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chinese vegetable salad
directions: Drain water off vegetables.
Mix sugar, water and vinegar in a large mixing bowl.
Add all vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Cover bowl and let set in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: In large mixing bowl mix pineapple and pistachio pudding well. Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Then add marshmallows and pecans. Place mixture in salad bowl.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet over medium heat, brown meat and cook onions until done.
Pour off drippings; stir in corn, tomato sauce, rice and steak sauce; set aside.
Cut top off peppers; remove seed and spoon mixture into peppers.
Arrange in baking dish; bake at 350° for 30
to 40 minutes.

title: potato-sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
In large casserole dish, layer potatoes, soup mixture and sausage.
Repeat layers, ending with sausage.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with cheese; heat until cheese melts.

title: salad mix up
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate in large dish and cut into squares.

title: m&m's cookie bar
directions: Mix oats, flour, brown sugar and melted butter; reserve 1 1/2 cups for later use.
Put the remaining in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix thawed lemonade, Cool Whip, milk and food coloring.
Pour into pie plate lined with crushed crackers and butter (melted). Chill.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Blend ingredients, then turn into pie plate.
Using tips of fingers, press into plate.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat a small amount of oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Drop by tablespoon into pan.
Fry until edges look dry.
Turn.
Fry until done.

title: potatoes, pasta and rice
directions: *Such as parsley, chives, thyme, sage or 2 to 3 teaspoons dried herbs (your choice).

title: english trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Thaw strawberries and prepare pudding according to package directions.
Take a sewing thread and moving it back and forth, cut one (9-inch) layer horizontally.
Place bottom half of the layer in a casserole dish. Layer with strawberries and pudding.
Place the top of the cake layer on top of this and top with another layer of strawberries and pudding.
Top with a thick layer of Cool Whip to fill the bowl.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill until served.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients through blender at highest speed.
The finer you can crush the ice, the better.
Makes about 3 glasses. Drink slowly, if not, you can get an instant headache.

title: fruit salad punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart container.
Add water and ice to fill container.

title: fig strawberry jam
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Place in jars.
Seal and let set one or two days before freezing.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Mix in large bowl and add dressing.

title: bucaroon cookies
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Add oats, chips, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together in mixer until blended.
The amount of horseradish can be adjusted according to taste.
Serve with crackers or bagel chips.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Roll bread as thin as possible.
Cook remaining ingredients over low heat for 5 minutes or until tender.
Place 1/2 of apple mixture on one slice of bread.
Moisten edges with water and fold over in a triangle.
Repeat with 2nd slice of bread.
Bake at 425° for 7 minutes or until browned.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In small bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and milk.
Beat well.
This frosting can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 2 weeks. Whip again before using.

title: mama's apple cobbler
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish or pan. Heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until crumbs are fine.
Add milk and stir with fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead just until smooth.
Roll dough into large rectangle, about 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Dampen the edge of dough with a little water and seal.
Slice dough into about 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Pour sugar syrup carefully over rolls.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat cream cheese and unprepared jello together.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Fold in fruit. (Make sure fruit is well drained.)
Chill and serve.

title: bacon and tomato casserole
directions: Cook
bacon;
drain
off
some grease.
Saute onion and pepper in the rest for about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes (chopped up), brown sugar, salt, pepper and seasoned pepper.
Pour into casserole; break bacon up into it and put toasted bread crumbs on top.
Dot with
butter.
Bake
at
for
minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: In 2-quart oblong baking dish, combine broccoli and cauliflower.

title: punch
directions: Mix and add 4 cups cold water.
Put in containers and freeze. Before serving, add 1 quart ginger ale in punch bowl with frozen punch.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter. Bring to a boil exactly 1 minute. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Drop by spoonful on aluminum foil and let harden.

title: munchy crunch
directions: Melt the chips together.
Add chow mein noodles and mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in water for 5 minutes, then stir until blended. Measure sugar, salt and shortening into mixing bowl.
Add hot milk and stir until shortening is broken into small lumps.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups of flour to make thick batter.
Beat 100 stokes until smooth and elastic.
Add yeast and eggs; stir until blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 to 2 cups flour and work in enough flour so dough isn't sticky.
Turn dough on floured board and knead for 2 minutes, about 100 strokes.
Shape in ball and put into greased bowl; let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down and use half to form small ball.
Dip in melted shortening and roll in a mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts. Arrange in tube pan rubbed with shortening and sprinkle with halves of pecans and seedless raisins.
Add another layer until half full.
Cover and let rise until double in size, about 50 minutes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn out of mold immediately and cool on cake rack.
Very delicious and fattening.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Simmer meat in water, just to cover, for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook onions in butter until golden.
Add meat to onions; cook until brown.
Add mushrooms.
Season with spices; simmer for 3 hours. Stir in sour cream over low flame, until well blended.
Serve over wide noodles.
Serves 4.

title: shepherd's bread dip
directions: Mix ingredients together; hollow out a loaf of Shepherd's bread forming a bowl.
Pour dip into bread bowl.
Use balance of bread, cut into small pieces, to dip.
Makes a great veggie dip, too.

title: orange glazed cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spices, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well blended.

Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are well moistened. Pour batter into two 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2-inch greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until done with wooden pick.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove to cooling racks. Completely cool bread, then drizzle with glaze.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Measure the 1 cup chopped.
Mix everything together and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Makes about 5 quarts. Can be frozen.

title: wyatt's pecan delight pie
directions: Whip egg whites on medium speed until soft peaks form. Continue whipping on medium speed while gradually adding sugar and baking powder.
Continue to whip until very stiff. Add vanilla and mix well.
Add the pecans and crackers; blend well.
Use a 9-inch Pyrex pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly brown.
When cool, add on top of pie the whipped cream.
Then sprinkle the 1/4 cup chopped pecans on the cream.

title: corn-stuffed tomato salad
directions: Place tomatoes, stem end down, on a cutting board.
Cut each into 4 to 6 wedges, cutting to but not through the stem end. Spread wedges apart, slightly.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover and chill.
In small mixing bowl, combine dressing, parsley, pepper and red pepper.
In another bowl, combine corn, cheese, bell pepper, cucumber and onions.
Add dressing mixture; toss gently to coat.
Cover; chill.
Serve tomatoes filled with corn mixture over lettuce on individual plates.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until thick.
Cool slightly. Add jello and stir until jello is dissolved.
Cover bottom of cooked, cooled pie shell with strawberries.
Add cornstarch jello mixture.
Top with whipped cream and chill well before serving.

title: baked ham with raisin sauce
directions: Wipe off ham
with damp cloth or soak in water, according to directions.
Put ham in roaster, skin side up.
Add one cup of water for
any
size ham.
Bake 15 minutes per pound at 350°.
Do not
open
roaster
during this time.
At the end of baking time, remove
ham
to
flat baking pan.
Peel off skin; score fat.
Top with
brown
sugar,
pineapple
rings
and/or cherries.
Blend 1/2 cup brown sugar and dry mustard.
Slowly add lemon
juice, lemon rind, flour, raisins and water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.

title: prize winning wheat 'n oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Crush cereal to 3/4 cup.
Beat egg.
Stir in milk, sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients just until moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Divide batter evenly into muffin cups.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion together in saucepan in small amount of water until tender.
Cool and drain.
Add beaten egg, 1 cup stuffing, milk, sugar, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in bottom of casserole dish.
Add squash mixture to dish.
Top with stuffing and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Put salmon in a 2-quart mixing bowl.
Add crumbled crackers and egg.
Mix well.
Make patties; roll in corn meal mix.
Fry in pan with 1/2 inch oil (hot).
Fry until golden brown.
Serve with French fries and salad.
Makes 12 patties.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Combine all.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll into balls about the size of small walnuts.
Dip one side into sugar and cinnamon, mixed.
Place balls, sugar side up, two inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in hot oven (375°) until lightly browned.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix together in a double boiler the soup, puree and seasonings.
Cook for 1 hour.
Saute onion and celery in butter; add to soup mixture.
Before serving, add soda and milk.
Do not boil.

title: salmon fillet
directions: Coat fish on both sides with olive oil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Squeeze on 1/2 to 1 lemon.
Top with slices of garlic and lemon.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cream the butter and sugars together. Add eggs and mix until blended. Add vanilla. Combine flour, salt, baking powder & cinnamon. Add to butter mixture on low speed.

title: cranberry peach cobbler
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, put pie filling and cranberry sauce in dish and mix up.
Put cake mix in bowl.
Add spices.
Put in margarine and mix until crumbly.
Put this on top of fruit mix. Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes until browned lightly.
Very good served warm.

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Steam squash until tender.
Mash squash.
Add onion, 1/2 cup bread crumbs, pepper, eggs, 1/2 stick butter, sugar and salt. Combine well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour squash in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and spread on top. Sprinkle with bread crumbs to suit taste.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs and bananas and applesauce. Stir in flour and soda. Pour into 2 loaf pans. Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Mix well and refrigerate. Makes 26 ounces.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef on medium heat until brown.
Add onion, celery and celery leaves and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in mushroom soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Pare potatoes and slice thinly.
Place half of the potatoes in a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spoon half of the ground beef mixture over potatoes, repeat with remaining potatoes, salt and meat mixture. Cover and bake in 400° oven for 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: church chicken
directions: Pour box of quick cooking rice into a 10 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch baking dish which you've buttered first.
Mix the milk and soups and pour over the rice.
Place uncooked frying chicken parts over the rice and sprinkle 1/2 package dry onion soup mixture over the top.
Cover the dish and bake in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours. Soups can be varied.

title: ginger lime punch
directions: Pour concentrate into a punch bowl.
Add candied ginger; chill 2 hours.
Add cold water, ice, sherbet and ginger ale.
Add rum, if desired.

title: sunday  brunch casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon; crumble and set aside. In the drippings, saute onion and green pepper until tender; remove with a slotted spoon. Beat eggs and milk in a large bowl. Stir in hash browns, cheese, salt, pepper, dill, onion, green pepper and bacon. Transfer to a greased 13x9x2 inch baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Yield 6-8 servings.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Shred cheeses.
Saute onions and butter.
Mix with other ingredients except grated Parmesan cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with Parmesan and brown using broiler.
Serve with tortilla chips, sour cream and salsa.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup sugar and margarine; mix until crumbly.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice; spread evenly over prepared crust.
Combine remaining 1 tablespoon sugar and cornstarch; stir in cranberry sauce.
Spoon evenly over cheese layer; top with crumb mixture.
Bake an additional 40 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 4 candy bars with 1/2 cup butter in saucepan, stirring constantly. Set aside. Cream sugar and 1/2 cup butter in mixer bowl until fluffy. Beat in flour and eggs. Stir in buttermilk, soda and 2 teaspoons vanilla. Fold in candy mixture. Spoon into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for 75 to 90 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool. Melt 2 candy bars and 1/2 cup butter with milk in saucepan, stirring constantly. Beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla and confectioners sugar. Frost cooled cake. Serves 16.

title: cornell oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
In separate large bowl, sift together flours, yeast, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add to first mixture.
Add raisins, wheat germ and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Arrange by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake until lightly browned at 375°, about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and	sugar
together.
Heat oleo, Crisco and cocoa in water.
Bring
to
a boil.
Pour boiling mixture over flour and sugar.
Add
beaten
eggs,	milk,
soda and vanilla. Mix thoroughly.
Bake in 9-inch pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Make well in center of mixture. Combine egg, milk, orange rind, orange juice and oil. Mix well and add to dry ingredients. Stir just enough to moisten. Stir in raisins. Spoon batter into greased muffin pan; fill 2/3 full. Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat tomato soup; add cream cheese.
It won't melt smooth, so mix with Mixmaster until smooth.
Add celery, peppers and onions; heat a few minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatine.
Add mayonnaise and shrimp.
Chill.
If it sits a while, the flavor goes through better.

title: barley and bacon casserole
directions: In 12-inch saute pan, melt butter and cook carrot and onion until softened, but not brown, about 3 minutes. Add barley and stir until grain turns golden, about 5 minutes.
Add warm chicken stock and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
The barley should be tender but not mushy.
Stir in celery and taste for seasoning. Let stand, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Serve topped with hot bacon. Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian noodle casserole
directions: Simmer onion, celery and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil. Add hamburger and brown very lightly. Add tomato paste and sauce, water and seasonings. Simmer 30 minutes. Cook noodles; drain. Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole. Layer noodles, meat and cheese; repeat layers. Bake 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice onion and pepper in thin round slices.
Mix with carrots. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: cheese pie
directions: Blend well.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with sprinkled nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Boil hamburger meat; add other ingredients.
Boil on low for one hour, stirring and mashing hamburger meat occasionally.
When done, spoon excess grease out.
If not enough chili powder, add to desired taste.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; butter.
Place in greased dish. Brown sausage.
Crumble and drain.
Sprinkle bread with cheese. Combine eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix. Pour over cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator fifteen minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 8.

title: bourbon beef tenderloin
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients.
Fold the tail end of the beef back onto itself so that the fillet is of uniform thickness; secure with butcher's string.
Pour marinade over meat; cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours, turning over several times during that period.
Cook over high heat on oiled grill, reserving marinade. Keep lid closed, but turn fillet often and baste with marinade occasionally.
Fillet is cooked rare in about 30 minutes, or when meat thermometer registers 115°.
Remove from fire and cover with foil to retain heat.
Let rest for 10 minutes so juices
stay in meat.

title: portobello mushroom, tomato and basil sandwich(heart healthy)
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the mushrooms and saut until brown and juicy, about 10 minutes.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook until tender.
Meanwhile, in a small skillet, saute onions in butter until tender.
Drain carrots; add onion, soup, mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: lemon slush cake
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine, 2 tablespoons sugar and flour and press in bottom of jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie shell.
Combine beaten eggs, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Grate cheese and fold into mixture.
Add bacon and onion rings.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° until golden brown, at least 15 or 20 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add onion and rice. Sprinkle salt and pepper on chicken.
Place chicken and pour soups over chicken.
Add water and bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown chicken.

title: crunch bars
directions: Spread saltines on buttered cookie sheet, spread with butter, sugar and bits.
Refrigerate.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put in heavy saucepan with sugar, cinnamon and water.
Place 8 biscuits on top.
Cover with lid and cook for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with custard sauce or ice cream.

title: old fashioned slush
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags, squeezing gently.
Add sugar and stir until it dissolves.
Stir in 6 cups of water, whiskey, frozen orange juice and frozen lemonade.
Cover and freeze at least 8 hours.

title: honeyed beets
directions: Cook beets; cut julienne.
Cook onion in oleo until tender. Stir in beets, honey, etc.
Heat until beets are hot.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: never fail chocolate fudge icing
directions: Bring these ingredients to a boil, then beat in enough powdered sugar so it will spread easily.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and spread on cake.

title: moist brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and cocoa together.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts.
Mix together with spoon, do not whip with mixer.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be a little soft in center when time is up.
Let cool.

title: orange congealed salad(serves 8)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; then add cold water.
Set aside.
Cook pineapple and sugar in saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Add to gelatin mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate for one hour.
After one hour, add whipped topping and cheese.
Pour into lightly greased gelatin mold.
Refrigerate until set. Unmold, cut and serve.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add other ingredients in layers as listed, in that order.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: aloha punch
directions: Thaw concentrated juices and combine in large jar.
Add water and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill well.
Add ginger ale.
Pour punch into punch bowl with blocks of ice.
With toothpick fix maraschino cherries in centers of pineapple slices. Float pineapple, banana and lime slices on punch.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: sausage macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water; drain.
Stir in margarine. Brown sausage; drain.
Add to macaroni.
Add salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Grated cheese may be added to top.

title: chocolate-peanut bars
directions: Combine honey, sugar and salt in saucepan; bring to a full boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, cereals and chocolate chips.
Press into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan. Chill 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 16 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Pour in cake pan.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour butter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter, then add milk evenly.
Add remaining ingredients in layers evenly.
Press down gently.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: toasted rice
directions: Toast rice in heavy uncovered pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Melt butter in heavy pan with tight fitting lid.

Brown rice slightly in the butter; pour in liquids and bring to a boil. Turn heat very low; cover and let steam for 25 to 30 minutes. Stir in finely chopped onions, including tops, and soy sauce. Remove from heat, but keep covered and let steam for a few more minutes.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Season to taste.
Place rice in baking dish.
Pour orange juice over rice.
Arrange browned pork chops on rice.
Pour soup over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onion on top of stove until tender.
Drain liquid and put in a casserole dish.
Mix with the soup and sour cream.
Fold in shredded carrots and cheese.
Melt 1 stick margarine and mix in the chicken stuffing mix.
Put half of the stuffing in the casserole and the rest on top of the casserole. Bake in oven until top of casserole is brown.

title: creamed cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn, cornmeal, melted butter, buttermilk, onion, eggs and baking soda.
Mix well.
Place half of batter into a 9-inch greased baking dish.
Cover evenly with 1 cup of cheese, then all of the diced peppers.
Cover with remaining batter and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: brown fig preserves
directions: Clean figs in water, remove stems and cut figs in half. (If desired, they can be left whole.) Place in a large pan, a dish pan works well. Put 5 pounds of sugar on top, heat stove to medium and cook for one minute. Then place on low setting and stir often for about 4 hours, until thickened and almost no juice. Allow to cool overnight. Sterilize canning lids, rings, funnel and dipping spoon in boiling water. Cook jars 10 to 20 minutes in a 200° oven. Place figs in jars, seal tightly and boil in a water canner 30 minutes. Cool overnight.

title: sweet and sour stew
directions: Combine flour, m.s.g. and pepper.
Coat beef with flour mixture. Brown in oil in kettle.
Combine water, catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over beef. Add onion and cook over low heat for about 45 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes or 2 hours until beef is done and vegetables are tender. Yields 6 servings.

title: alexis' brown sugar chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter until smooth.
Add the sugars.
Beat in the eggs and vanilla.
Sift the flour, salt and soda.
Beat into the butter mixture.
Add the chocolate chips. Drop 2 to 3 tablespoon of batter onto greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 minutes.
Remove from pans with spatula and cool on racks.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Cook rice and celery in chicken broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Remove chili pod before serving.

title: slim-jim baked chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with garlic salt, rubbing well into the flesh.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place in a shallow baking pan, skin side down.
Place larger pieces in the corner and smaller ones in the center.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.

title: pizza(better than traditional)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly oil 12-inch pizza pan. Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, 4 1/2 teaspoons basil or 1/2 teaspoon dried basil, 1/4 teaspoon dried oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Press dough into pan.
Cover with sauce.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining basil and oregano.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Garnish with fresh basil, if desired.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs together with the sugar.
Mix this with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a pie pan and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots, celery and onions in water until tender. Add milk, butter and potato flakes until soup is of desired thickness.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-cook the eggs, then immediately crack eggshells and plunge into cold water for a few minutes and slip off the shells. Cut into halves and remove yolks.
Mash yolks with deviled ham and parsley.
Pile mixture into egg white halves and arrange on serving dish.
Garnish with crisp vegetable relishes and green olives.

title: oat and wheat bran muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mash bananas, whisk in egg, milk, oil and sugar. Stir liquids into dry mixture.
Add apricots.
Spoon batter into non-stick muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix with milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Spread layer in bottom of dish and cover with a layer of vanilla wafers, layer of sliced bananas and a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat until all is used.
Reserve some Cool Whip for topping.

title: broiled on peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on warm or cooled cakes.
Broil 2 to 4 minutes.
Watch carefully to avoid burning.

title: hobo stew(low-fat)
directions: Combine and simmer for 1 hour until vegetables are cooked. Serve with Parmesan cheese, bread and butter.

title: chocolate chip bread
directions: Pour warm water into bowl.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add margarine, egg, milk, brown sugar, 2 tablespoons white sugar, salt, cinnamon and warmed chocolate chips.
Stir until very evenly mixed.
Add bread flour, one cup at a time, constantly stirring.
Beat until dough is smooth and elastic.
Mix at least 10 minutes.
Dump mixture onto floured board.
Flour hands; knead 10 to 15 minutes.
Put dough into lightly greased bowl. Let rise until doubled in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
"Rise place" should be warm, dark and draft free.
Take dough out of bowl; knead it down a few seconds.

title: oatmeal jumbles
directions: Sift flour and add soda.
Measure shortening and next six ingredients into large bowl.
Beat vigorously with spoon or electric mixer until well mixed.
Stir in flour, oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix everything but Cool Whip.
Place in pan.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir all together and put in greased dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: country skillet dinner
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in frying pan and cook until beef is brown.
Drain excess grease.
Add tomato paste, water, oregano, cumin and noodles.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put 1/2 of mixture in large casserole dish.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Use remainder of mix and more Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine in measuring cup
the
juice and grated rind of an orange plus 2 tablespoons shortening.
Fill cup to 3/4 full with boiling water.
Pour
into	mixing	bowl
and
beat.
Add sugar, berries and nuts.
Add egg.
Mix together.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind together and add sugar.
Mix well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add egg, water and vanilla and beat together until creamy by hand.
Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by heaping teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Mix walnuts and margarine in 9-inch pie plate until well blended.
Press into bottom and up sides of pie plate. Refrigerate.
Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in large bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
(Stir until chocolate is completely melted.)
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk until well blended.
Refrigerate until cooled. Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Spoon in crust. Freeze 4 hours.
Garnish as desired.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes or until pie can be easily cut.

title: pickled beans
directions: Mix together cold water, vinegar and salt.
Cook beans until almost done.
Wash in cold water.
Pack beans in quart jars and fill with water mixture leaving a small space at the top of the jar.
Seal tightly.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients.
Pour in liquid ingredients and stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in pecans; spoon into two greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: one step lasagna in microwave(serving size: 6)
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper.

In large oblong baking dish, spoon 1/2 cup sauce (cover bottom of dish), add a layer of uncooked noodles, a layer of meat and sauce mixture, a layer of egg and cottage cheese mixture and a layer of Mozzarella.
Repeat layers. Cover with plastic wrap.
Heat on High for 8 minutes, then cook for 30 to 32 minutes on Medium-high (I use 50% power).
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: country style chicken dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine potatoes and 1/2 can fried onions.
In small bowl, blend soup and milk.
Pour 1/2 over potato mixture.
Arrange cheese slices over potato mixture.
Top with chicken, skin side down.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins and bacon in large bowl; mix well. Mix sweetened condensed milk, vinegar, mustard, egg, salt and pepper in bowl.
Add desired amount of dressing to broccoli mixture; toss well.
Top salad with onion rings.
Chill for several hours to several days.
May store dressing in refrigerator for several days.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: caramel orange
directions: Place the sliced oranges in a flat dish; pour over the curacao or Grand Marnier and allow to soak.
Place sugar and 1 tablespoon water in a small saucepan over high heat and keep shaking the pan to avoid burning.
Do not stir.
As soon as caramel is pale brown, pour over the oranges.
Allow to cool before serving.
Serves 4.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind or put in food processor the first 3 ingredients, then mix with pizza sauce.
Spread over open buns.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles, about 18 to 20 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and beat again.
Add egg, molasses and beat.
Add remaining ingredients which have been sifted together.
(I put dough in refrigerator until it's firm and use a glass to press down before baking.)
Roll dough into balls size of small walnuts.
Roll in sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Blend in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Alternate layers of wafers, bananas and pudding, ending with pudding layer.
Chill and serve.

title: hollandaise carrots
directions: Place all ingredients in covered saucepan (or frying pan) and cook over very low heat.
Shake once in a while to keep from burning.

title: bleu cheese cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, together. Form into a ball. Place on a flat plate. Pat chopped nuts over the cheese ball. Refrigerate to set the flavors. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill until set.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch together; then pour into egg yolks that have been well beaten.
Pour scalded milk into this mixture.
Put in top of a double boiler and stir while cooking until mixture is thick.
Add butter, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together all but the Cool Whip and pecans.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Add the pecans. Freeze overnight in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut and serve when needed.

title: hamburger sauce
directions: Mix all together; warm up in a kettle.
Pour over 20 hamburger patties in a pan; put in the oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until hamburgers are done.

title: italian salsa
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in to bowl of a food processor.
Pulse for about 10 seconds to break the cheese into small pieces.
Scrape sides and pulse again.
Transfer to a large mixing bowl.
Add lemon juice and basil and mix thoroughly.
Add salt to taste.
Add tomato and avocado before serving.
Serve chilled.

title: salmon pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss the pasta, salmon, tomatoes, cucumber and onion.
For dressing, combine the oil, lemon or lime juice, dill, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour over pasta.
Cover and chill.
Serve over lettuce.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: baptist cookies
directions: Mix together and cook on top of stove in an iron skillet until all is melted.
Remove from fire and add Rice Krispies and nuts. Cool and roll into balls and roll in Angel Flake coconut.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Set butter out to soften.
Then mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour or overnight.
Roll out, cut and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
You can brush the dough with food coloring (mixed with water) to match the holiday.
Then sprinkle with sugar.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes, no longer.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a well-greased pan. Bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Mix all together and cook at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes, just until the onions are done.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut stick of oleo into pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over oleo.
Place chicken over rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix both soups and water together and pour over the chicken; cover.
Bake at 275° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: herbed spinach
directions: Cook spinach in small amount of water; drain well.
Combine spinach with soup, cheese and onions and pour into greased baking dish.
