Combine stuffing mix with butter; sprinkle over spinach and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cocktail party pate
directions: Mix in	electric
mixer
or
food processor fitted with steel knife.
Beat
liverwurst until softened.
Add butter and cream cheese and	blend
until light and fluffy.	Add parsley, onion, brandy and	curry
powder.	Add salt and pepper.
Spoon into serving container.	Cover and chill.
Serve with crudites and assorted crackers.

title: texas soup
directions: Put all in a large pot (do not drain any of the vegetables). For seasoning add 1 envelope taco seasoning and 1 envelope Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix.
Stir all together and heat at least 30 minutes.
It's ready!

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.
Dice pepper.
Mix all ingredients except meat and cheese. Grease 9-inch cast-iron skillet and heat in oven.
Place 1/2 of cornbread mixture in hot skillet.
Add meat, then cheese.
Top with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Refrigerate at least one to two hours before using.

title: poulet de france
directions: In a medium bowl, mix stuffing, melted margarine and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Mix chicken, 3/4 cup broth, onions, chives, celery, mayonnaise and salt in another bowl.
Spread half the stuffing in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish treated with nonstick spray.
Spread chicken mixture over stuffing.
Cover with remaining stuffing. Whisk eggs, milk and soup in a large bowl.
Pour sauce evenly over stuffing.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated oven at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 more minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Add all vegetables, seasonings, rice and chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until rice and vegetables are tender.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add apples.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Mix all together; dough will be very stiff. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Saute seasonings with meat.
Add soup, beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cut tortillas in fourths.
Put 1/2 of these in greased casserole dish.
Pour half of meat mixture on this and cover with half of the cheese; repeat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Set aside about 10 minutes before serving.

title: surprise kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add flour and nuts; blend well.

Shape about 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy, covering it completely. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 7 to 10 minutes, or until set but not brown.	Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.
Store airtight.
Makes 36 to 48.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: In large bowl mix lard with flour.
Work up real good.
Add milk.
Work well.
Turn oven on 350°.
Makes sure it is hot.
Put flour on whatever you like and put your dough on it.
Work it. Cut out.
Put in greased pan.
Put in hot oven.
Cook about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wilted lettace salad
directions: Fry bakon 'til crisp.
Drain fat, leavin' bakon in skillet. Krumble bakon.
Add vinegah, watah, onion, salt, sugah 'n peppah to skillet.
Heat 'til hit boils.

title: chili
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook onions and garlic in 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
In a large pot over medium heat, cook beef and turkey until meat is evenly crumbled and has lost all pink color.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients and stir for several minutes.
Cover pot and cook on medium for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: mystery barbecue sauce
directions: These ingredients were in a "secret" barbecue sauce.
The person revealing the ingredients to me said that he would reveal the ingredients only, but not the quantities of each.
So, you see, you must experiment with the ingredients to your own particular taste.
The barbecue sauce that I tasted originally was the best I had ever had.
Good luck.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter together and then press lightly into a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.

title: cherry or strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix everything together well and freeze. Keep frozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; then add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape with hands into large ball (or smaller individual ones).
Roll in cracker crumbs or finely chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in baking dish set into a pan containing about one-inch of water.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Test for doneness by inserting knife in center of casserole.
Corn is done when knife comes out clean and uncoated. Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, pepper and Wesson oil together.
Pour corn and tomatoes in oblong cake pan.
Cook macaroni and pour into pan with corn and tomatoes, adding hamburger mixture, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and garlic.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 people.

title: supreme rice casserole(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Cover tightly and microwave 5 minutes on High.
Stir and microwave 5 additional minutes on 50% power.
Let stand several minutes before serving. Simply scrumptious!

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks and sweetened milk and add lime juice.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake for 30 minutes. Cool. Chill.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake chicken breasts until done.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream of chicken soup and the sour cream.
Be sure to blend well. Tear chicken into bite-size pieces and place in an oblong pan. Pour soup mixture over it.
Sprinkle several poppy seed over this and top with croutons.
The ones with sage provide a flavor of dressing.
Bake at 400° until heated through.

title: italian salad
directions: Place in large skillet and simmer with 1/2 cup water.
Bring to a boil and simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate 24 hours.
Drain well before serving.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can onions.
Pour mixture into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remainder of cheese and fried onions and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Chop corned beef.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake in a greased dish, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in 4-quart saucepan.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.
Mix remaining ingredients together until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cake layers
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and flour, starting and ending with flour.
Make 4 layers.
Bake at 350°.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook meats together until well done. Add jar spaghetti sauce to meat and simmer for 10 min. Mix cottage cheese with egg and oregano in a bowl. Line a 9x13 pan with raw lasagne.
Put cottage cheese mixture on noodles. Spoon sauce on top, sprinkle cheese. Repeat layers andend with cheese on top.
Bake cover for 45-50 min in 350° oven. Put knife through noodle to make sure it goes through. Let stand for about 10 min. before cutting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onions in butter.
Add cooked broccoli, soup and cheese.
Mix and turn contents into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook the frozen vegetables as directed on the package.
Drain. Add the diced raw vegetables.

title: crabmeat patties
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in oleo.
Mix with other ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Dip in cracker crumbs. May fry or bake.

title: flautas
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; stir and heat on low until cheese melts.
Crumb sausage and ground beef together in skillet and cook, but don't brown.
Drain grease.
Add 2 cans of chili salsa to the meat and cook until most of the liquid is evaporated. Spread tortillas with hot bean mixture.
Spread meat over beans. Roll tortillas and place seam side down in a single layer in a large well-greased baking pan.
Pour remaining can of salsa on top.
Sprinkle with Colby cheese, tomatoes and green onion tops. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve each Flauta on a bed of shredded lettuce and top with a dollop of sour cream. Serves 8.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Beat the eggs; add the sugar and beat.
Mix the flour, baking powder and salt together and add to the egg and sugar mixture. Fold in the fruit and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry cheesecakes
directions: Blend the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Line small foil cups with vanilla wafers (flat side up).
Fill 1/2 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Spoon on prepared blueberry filling.

title: oven baked nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam; line pan with round nachos.
(Try to use unbroken pieces.)
Spoon a little meat on each chip.
Drop a little sour cream on the meat, followed by a slice of jalapeno pepper on each.
Put shredded cheese on each one and place in oven until slightly melted.
Remove from oven and let cool slightly.
Enjoy!

title: flossie's chicken and dressing
directions: Mix cornbread and chicken broth.
Add all other ingredients. Mixture will be thin.
Place in large pan or baking dish and bake at 350° to 400° until done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill a cup 1/2 full of mix; add hot water to make 1 cup hot chocolate.

title: leb cake
directions: Mix well. Spread in layers in oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown. Cut in squares while hot and ice with white glaze.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in tightly covered container.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to a cup of hot water for tea.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix meal, flour, sugar and salt together; add water and milk to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Melt Crisco in baking pan.
Pour mixture in baking pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: mexican corn
directions: Mix together the flour, meal, milk, egg, salt, corn and oil. Brown hamburger, onion, cumin and hot pepper.
Place 2 cups of corn meal mixture in greased, hot iron skillet.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of cheese.
Place hamburger mixture over this.
Add rest of cheese and top with rest of corn meal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bridge dessert
directions: Beat milk into pudding and blend in sour cream.
Layer half of the angel food in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread pudding over cake, then pie filling, then Cool Whip.
Best made the day before.

title: beef stew
directions: Melt margarine in pan on stove.
Brown meat with onion, salt and pepper added.
Place potatoes, green beans, carrots and water over meat.
Cover and bake in the oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Return to stove.
Make a paste of 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.
Stir into stew to thicken broth.

title: peanut butter cookies with chocolate chunks
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking soda and salt in medium bowl. Using electric mixer, beat peanut butter, brown sugar, butter, honey, egg and vanilla in large bowl until well blended. Stir dry ingredients into peanut butter mixture in 2 additions. Stir in chopped chocolate. Cover and refrigerate until dough is firm and no longer sticky. Preheat oven to 350°. Butter 2 large baking sheets. With hands, roll 1 heaping tablespoon of dough for each cookie into 1 3/4-inch balls. Place cookies on baking sheets 2 1/2-inches apart. Bake cookies until puffed and beginning to brown on top, but still soft to touch, about 12 minutes. Cool on baking sheets 5 minutes. Using metal spatula, transfer cookies to rack to cool completely.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer, the longer the better.

title: kraut salad
directions: Wash and rinse kraut.
Wash again.
Add celery and onion.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar together and pour over vegetable mixture. Let stand overnight.

title: best carrot salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate or serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour in a baked 9-inch pie crust.
Beat egg whites and brown on top of pie.

title: easy dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Use all of Stove Top. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sage to taste.
Add broth as needed to keep mixture moist.
Add enough broth so mixture will not be dry.
Pour in dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grandma gray's venison
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oleo in large cast-iron frypan.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and sage.
Dip venison pieces into mixture and place in hot pan turning once until done.

title: kurabia cookies
directions: Cream butter thoroughly and add sugar.
Mix well.
Then gradually add flour until
mixture becomes pliable.
Roll into desired shape. May be topped with blanched almond halves.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for about 20 minutes or until almonds are browned.

title: down south potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and butter, mixing until blended.
Add sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Blend in eggs and milk.
Pour into crusts and bake in a 350° oven 1 hour.

title: pecan pie(syrupless)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat eggs and sugar until mixed.
Blend in the flour, buttermilk, butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add pecans and pour into pie shell that has been baked for 10 minutes.
Bake about 30 to 40 more minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Power level on High, 8 to 11 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Shape into balls and press with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Makes about 9 to 10 dozen.

title: bibingca
directions: Melt the butter.
Combine all the ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour the mixture into a greased oblong pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Prepare gelatin in usual manner using 1 less cup of water. Pour 1/2 of mixture in large salad mold.
Let congeal.
Spread carton of sour cream on top and add remainder of gelatin mixture.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, beef and rice. Stir
over high heat until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce
and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring quickly to a
boil. Cover tightly and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Pour in milk. Stir over high heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly. When mixture begins to thicken, add butter and vanilla.
Stir until forms hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat and stir until fudge loses its gloss.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a buttered dish.
Let cool.
Cut into squares with a buttered knife.

title: copper penny
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Make marinade with liquid.
Beat well.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli flowerets and stems, onion, raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon pieces in salad bowl. Then make the dressing of vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise. Put over the salad just before serving.

title: turkey sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties and brown.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except beans. Stir well. Add beans and bake slowly at 250° to 300° for 4 hours.

title: roasted red peppers and chicken pasta
directions: Boil pasta as package directs. Cook chicken and garlic in a 12-inch nonstick skillet, generously coated with cooking spray, over medium heat until lightly brown. Add bouillon granules, water, roasted red peppers, mushrooms, parsley and olives. Cover and simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes. Stir in pasta; heat through. Serve immediately. Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: turkey-apple bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except chili sauce and mix lightly.
Press into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Top with chili sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is cooked through.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: refreshing punch
directions: Mix together in a large punch bowl.
(If more is needed, add 1 more can of Hawaiian Punch and 1 quart 50/50.) Serves 25 people.

title: marinated salad
directions: In
bowl
combine all ingredients.
Marinate overnight. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.

title: tangy sausage
directions: Mix sauce and add to sausage.
Bake covered in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serve hot in a crock-pot dish.
Better if made ahead.
Add chunks of pineapple for that "little something extra."

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients together except carrots. Add cooled carrots and mix thoroughly.
Marinate for 2 or 3 days.
When carrots are used up, add more.
Keeps for 4 weeks.

title: pull apart vegetable bread
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and chives in butter.
Quarter biscuits.
Combine all ingredients (be sure biscuits are well-coated with butter).
Pour into ungreased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Soak tomatoes 24 hours in lime solution.
Rinse well at least 4 times.
Combine vinegar, spices, sugar, and salt;
add tomatoes and cook for 30 minutes.
Remove tomatoes from the mixture. Continue to cook the mixture until it
becomes a thick syrup. Pack tomatoes into sterilized jar;
pour hot syrup over and seal immediately.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie crust. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage and cabbage pot pie
directions: Cook sausage and onion in Dutch oven, stirring occasionally, until sausage is done; drain.
Stir in sugar, salt, cabbage and tomatoes; break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare pie crust mix as directed for one crust.
Shape pastry to fit top of 2-quart casserole.
Mix flour and cold water; stir into hot sausage mixture.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Place pastry over sausage mixture.
Seal around edges.
Slit top for steam to escape.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until crust is brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift flour into this mixture.
Add water and mix until smooth. Pour into loaf pans or muffin tins. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Choose at least 4.
Suggestions:
carrots, squash, cucumbers, green onions, cauliflower, broccoli flowerets, tomatoes, green and red pepper, olives, etc.

title: swedish parsnip souffle
directions: Cook carrots covered in small amount of boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: louise's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 teaspoons sugar in warm water. Let stand 2 minutes. Add milk, sugar, shortening, salt and eggs.
Blend in flour until you have a soft dough.
Knead.
Turn in greased bowl. Let rise until double.
Punch down and make hot rolls.
Let rise again. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles a few minutes.
Cook celery and onions 4 or 5 minutes.
Fold everything together in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: homemade pasta
directions: Mix flour together, make a circle of flour.
Make a hole in the middle.
Place eggs in middle of flour and softly beat eggs in center of flour.
Slowly add flour to eggs from each side and mix with eggs until completely blended.
Knead dough, add a sprinkle of flour if sticky.
Continue kneading (fold toward you and push away), turn dough and continue folding and pushing away from you and turning for about 5 minutes.
Let dough rest about 15 minutes. Give a couple pushes and folds (make ball).
Cut a piece the size of an egg, flatten and put in stretcher, take out, fold, add flour and repeat about 4 times.
Change notch smaller and stretch again. Add spaghetti attachment and put dough through machine.
Can be folded and stored for a few days or eat today.

title: old time beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven brown meat in 2 tablespoons hot shortening, turning often.
Add 2 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: easy black forest torte
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Prepare cake batter according to package directions; pour over marshmallows. Spoon pie filling over batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool. Frost with whipped topping. Store in the refrigerator.

title: my old kentucky home pecan pie
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and butter.
Mix well, then add pecans.
Pour into the unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and stir.
Add tomatoes and Doritos just before serving and stir.

title: rainbow finger jello
directions: Mix 1 (3 ounce) jello and 1 package Knox gelatine (be sure to mix these 2 ingredients together dry before adding boiling water). Add 1 cup boiling water and stir until dissolved.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Mix 6 cups water with 4 cups sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and allow to cool completely.
Blend bananas until smooth.
Add bananas, lemon juice, orange juice and pineapple juice to sugar-water mixture.
Freeze until firm.
Thaw to mushy stage and add 2 bottles club soda.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: pear and apple conserve
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Bring slowly to a boil and cook until mixture is clear.
Pack in hot jars and seal at once.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, cocoa and milk for 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla; mix.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool and harden.
Enjoy!

title: easy cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Add salt, Accent, garlic and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add butter, milk and cream; heat to boiling.
Mix flour and water in jar.
Shake until smooth.
Add to soup, stirring until thickened.

title: fresh fruit pasta salad
directions: Cook shells 14 minutes.
Mix in small bowl the yogurt and orange juice.
Mix rest of ingredients with shells.
Add yogurt dressing and mix well.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Sift cake mix into large mixer bowl and add pudding mix, eggs, oil, club soda and nuts. Beat batter at medium-high speed for 4 minutes (this is very important). Pour batter into a greased Bundt, tube or 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool completely; frost.

title: cream cheese pudding
directions: Prepare pudding or pie filling mix as directed.
Cool until lukewarm.
With high speed mixer, whip softened cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in pudding until smooth.
Serve as pudding or pie filling.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift flour once, then measure.
Add baking powder and salt. Sift three times.
Cream butter thoroughly and add sugar gradually.
Continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites carefully.
Bake in greased eight-inch pans at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: trash bag mix
directions: Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter; melt in microwave or on stove until smooth.
In large bowl (must have room enough for mixing), combine Rice Chex, pretzels, raisins and nuts; pour chocolate mixture over cereal and mix until well coated.
In large white trash bag, place powdered sugar, then pour in coated cereal mixture.
Tie bag and toss until all items are coated. Spread on wax paper to dry 10 minutes.
Store in containers.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in a baked or graham cracker pie shell. Refrigerate for several hours.

title: single serving pudding
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and cornstarch in a 1-quart glass bowl and stir well.
Gradually add milk.
Stir well.
Microwave milk mixture on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave on Medium-high for 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Add vanilla extract and stir well.
You may double mixture. Do not forget the whipped cream! Enjoy!

title: oreo mud pie
directions: Crush cookies and keep 1 cup of cookies for top.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix the cinnamon and applesauce.
Add the glue; mix again. Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Use toothpick to make the hole for hanging the ornament with ribbon, etc.
Let dry.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together and cook until soft ball forms in cold water. Remove from heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Watch closely because it takes a couple minutes to cook.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour and measure 2 cups; add salt and baking powder and sift again.
Cut in margarine until fine mixture.
Gradually add milk to make a soft dough.
Flour wax paper or dough board.
Pour soft dough onto floured paper or dough board and knead several times then firmly pat out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with floured cutter.
Makes 12 to 18 biscuits depending on thickness.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 12 minutes.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 30 minutes and serve.

title: the best apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut Crisco into flour like pie crust.
Roll out on floured board into large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle cinnamon over apples; toss well.
Spread apples over dough and roll up jelly roll style.
Dampen edges of dough with water and pinch to seal.
Slice into about 16 (1/2-inch) slices.

title: beef and spinach supreme
directions: Brown the first 5 ingredients and cook 3 minutes.

Meanwhile, combine spinach, soup, sour cream and rice. Add meat mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted. Cut into squares. Can be made a day ahead. Freeze leftover portions for later use.

title: texas caviar
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients together.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 2 hours, better if it sits all night.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips, also good on warm tortillas or as a taco topping.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Heat soup; blend in cream cheese and Knox gelatine.
Let cool. Add balance of ingredients and place in a well-greased mold pan. Let set until ready.

title: mary k's
directions: Melt carob chips in microwave or on stove.
Add other ingredients.
Spoon trail mix onto wax paper and cool.
Eat.

title: confetti dip
directions: Cook, until thickened, eggs, vinegar and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: ernie's fudge pie
directions: Over very low heat or in microwave, melt butter and chocolate squares.
Place eggs in mixing bowl and beat until light.
Add syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla to beaten eggs; beat again.
Add slightly cooled chocolate mixture to egg and sugar mixture.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is crusty and filling is set but still somewhat soft inside.
Do not overbake.
Pie should shake like custard so it will not be too stiff when cool.
Can serve plain, but is best served with a topping of a thin spade of vanilla ice cream.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put cinnamon and 3/4 cup of sugar in plastic bag and shake biscuits that have been quartered in mixture.
Place in Bundt or tube pan.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Pour this mixture over biscuit pieces in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: strawberry black bottom pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat half and half in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Beat smooth with wire whisk. Remove from heat. Whisk in egg yolks one at a time, mixing well.
Blend. Return to heat.
Cook, stirring 1 to 2 minutes longer. Cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set, 2 to 3 hours.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix 1 large box grape jello according to directions.
Add 1 can blueberry pie filling.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Add to jello mixture, mix well.
Pour in casserole dish and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Mix sour cream, 1 pkg. cream cheese, 1 c. sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla and spread on top of jello mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain fat.
Mix other ingredients in. Add beef and onions.
Put in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
You can freeze it or you can warm it and eat.
Serves 6.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage.
Melt cheese and add Ro-Tel. Add meat to Ro-Tel and cheese.
Thin with milk as desired.

title: royal chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Brown chicken in butter and set aside.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and shortening, cutting until well blended.
Beat egg until light; add to water and vinegar.
Add this to flour mixture and mix well.
Roll as needed.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in pie shell.
Lightly beat eggs in a bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 7 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together in a large bowl or grocery sack.
Store in airtight containers.
Use approximately 1/4 cup mix to 3/4 cup boiling water.
Great to take camping!

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Strawberry Fluff is made in 3 layers and the layers must be prepared in sequence.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar,
cocoa and flour well.
Separate eggs and add yolks to
mixture.
Slowly
add the water and mix until smooth. Cook in top
of
double
boiler until thick.
Pour into baking dish.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add add ingredients to a crock pot and allow to melt.
Serve warm with Frito Lay Scoops.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and put into big soup pot.
Add celery, salt and pepper.
Cover with water.
Put on lid.
Simmer until chicken falls off bones.
Drain broth.
Debone chicken.
Discard bones and celery.
Add chicken and corn into broth.
Bring to a boil.

title: cheese custard
directions: Put grated cheese in baking dish, 1/3 full.
Beat the whole eggs; add salt, pepper, grated onion and milk.
Pour egg and milk mixture over cheese and top with a few pieces of butter.
Place in baking dish in pan of water and bake in slow oven for 1 hour.
May be left longer.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After done and while hot, punch holes with fork all over and pour the can of cream of coconut over the cake.
When it is completely cool, frost with the Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk which have been mixed together.

title: chili soup
directions: Saute onion until golden brown.
Add tomatoes, meat, beans and seasonings.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Add water, if needed.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Add this to mixture.

title: grandma's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake cookies 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Time may vary according to oven.

title: sour cherry crumb pie
directions: Mix tapioca and 1/3 cup sugar together.
Layer cherries in 1 unbaked 9-inch pie crust, in thirds, alternating them with a sprinkling of the tapioca and sugar mixture.

title: port wine jello mold(double batch)
directions: Drain cherries and oranges; reserve juices.
Pour juices into 1-quart measuring cup and add enough water to make 6 cups liquid. Heat juices to boiling over medium heat.
Add jello and stir well. Cool slightly and stir in wine.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into mold. Grease pans with oil.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake or brownies as directed on package; let cool. Crumble Heath bars in blender.
Mix pudding as directed on box, then mix Cool Whip in with pudding.
Crumble cake.
Layer cake, then pudding, then candy; repeat layers.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle crumbled candy on top of this. Refrigerate!

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and raisins.
Pull thawed bread dough into walnut size pieces (35 balls).
Fill pan single layers, in rows.
Heat together butter and sugar; do not boil.
Take off heat and add milk and dry vanilla pudding fast. Stir quickly and pour over dough.
Cover and allow to rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or less.
Let stand 5 minutes, then invert on foil on cookie sheet.

title: morning lift-off
directions: In a blender, mix orange juice, oatmeal and honey with bananas for 1 minute on medium speed.
Add cereal, tofu and wheat germ; blend for 1 more minute.
Makes 5 cups.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar.
Beat eggs and add.
Put in bread and pineapple.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat first seven ingredients together by hand.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 2/3 of batter in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of chips mixture over batter.
Pour and spread rest of batter over this, then sprinkle rest of chips mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger and cabbage casserole
directions: Combine browned hamburger, cabbage, onion and garlic and put in casserole dish.
Combine milk and soup and pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (375° for glass).
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan in oven. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients in order:
chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts.
Press down. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until light brown. Cool.
Chill, if desired. Cut into bars and store at room temperature.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Mix together cream cheese, cottage cheese and 2 raw eggs.
Mix well with mixer. Boil noodles until tender (do not overcook).
In a large pan, layer sauce on bottom, noodles, sauce, cream cheese mixture, boiled eggs and Mozzarella cheese. Continue layering until gone or you run out of room.
Bake at 425° for approximately 45 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes before cutting.
If too soupy, cook longer; too dry, decrease cooking time.

title: stir up apple cake
directions: Sift together first 8 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir all together.
Bake in greased 9-inch angel food pan or loaf pan at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: mozzarella sticks
directions: Coat cheese in flour, then dip into buttermilk and then into bread crumbs. Fry in oil until golden. Drain on paper towels. Garnish with basil. Serve hot.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry beef, green pepper and onions in shortening.
Mix the rest of the ingredients in a pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: paper sack apple pie
directions: Chop apples into small pieces.
Place half of apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix spices with 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle half of this over apples.
Repeat.

title: willard scott's favorite christmas cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix together all ingredients with an electric mixer. Spray three 9-inch round cake pans with nonstick coating. Pour batter equally into the 3 pans and bake for 20 minutes. Test for doneness with a toothpick. Cool layers in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Carefully remove layers from pans to rack to cool completely.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Combine and pour into mold or bowl and let set.

title: blintzes
directions: Reserve crepes.
Combine cottage cheese, granulated sugar replacement, vanilla and lemon peel in mixing bowl.
Whip with fork until thoroughly blended.
Fill each crepe with heaping 1 tablespoon (15 ml) of cottage cheese filling; roll each on to form blintzes and place in shallow pan.
Bake at 350°F (175°C) for 15 minutes or until warm.
Sift the powdered sugar replacement over the blintzes.

title: spinach sausage pie
directions: Brown sausage, breaking up meat with a spoon; drain off fat and cool.
Lightly beat eggs in a large bowl (save 1 tablespoon of egg to brush on top crust).
Add cheeses, spices, spinach and sausage, mixing until well combined.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan or spray with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Crumble nuts in bottom of pan.
In large bowl, mix cake mix and instant pudding with eggs and liquids.
Mix well (about 2 minutes).
Pour into pan on top of pecans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from oven; pour on hot rum glaze.
Cake will settle.
Let cool in pan 30 minutes.
Loosen edges; turn upside-down on plate.
Nuts will be on top.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crispy raw vegetables.

title: "taramosalata" - fish roe dip or spread
directions: Put tamara in cheesecloth and rinse several times in cold water.
Put the salad and olive oil in a bowl.
Cut the bread, crusts removed, into small pieces.
Beat the tarama with electric mixer, adding a tablespoon lemon juice alternately with the oil and soaked in water bread, beating well after each addition.
Continue until all lemon juice and bread are used.
Fold in onion and parsley.
If mixture is too thick, add a little cold water.
Serve on squares of bread or crackers.

title: irish bread
directions: Boil raisins for 3 minutes; strain.
Sprinkle with a little flour and set aside.
Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, oil, milk and eggs.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° in oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook until it spins a thread.
Pour over popcorn.
Put butter on hands and press together to form balls.
Wrap individually.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine melted together and put in bottom of large pan for crust.
Save some crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Pour in cherry pie filling.
Mix Dream Whip as on package with chilled milk; add cream cheese and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Chill for about 1 hour.

title: cinderella quiche
directions: In bowl toss cheese with flour.
Add half and half and remaining ingredients.
Pour into shell bake 55-60 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15-20 minutes after you remove from oven to make cutting easier.

title: short bread cookies
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, margarine, and sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Shape teaspoons of dough into balls and press half a cherry in the center of cookie.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool; sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: salsa
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil and simmer at least 30 minutes (3 to 4 hours in slow cooker).
Process in sterilized pint and 1/2 pint jars in hot water bath for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 pints.

title: salmon stew
directions: Stew potatoes and onion until done; add salmon, butter and salt and pepper to taste, then add as much milk as desired.

title: rice chicken casserole
directions: Grind or chop celery, onions and pepper.
Fry sausage and remove from pan.
Fry chopped vegetables in fat.
Add meat.
Cook rice in 5 cups boiling water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add Lipton soup and cook 7 minutes.
Add vegetables, meat and canned soup and milk. Pour into 2 shallow baking pans and bake slowly for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Make 3 depressions in dry ingredients.
Pour vinegar into one, vanilla into one and oil into one.
Pour water over all.
Mix well until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.
Serve with cream, Cool Whip or frosting.

title: fresh apple nut bread
directions: In large
bowl,
cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt, lemon rind, nuts, spices and grated apple.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Turn
into
a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan. Bake in preheated
350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: husbands delight casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add seasonings, sugar and tomato sauce. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Cook noodles as directed on package. Blend onions, sour cream and cream cheese. Grease 2 1/2 qt. casserole. Alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce, sour cream and grated cheese. End with layer of cheddar cheese. Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serves: 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with salt and ginger.
Shape into balls.
Beat egg slightly with water; dip balls into egg mixture, then flour to coat well.
Brown in salad oil in large skillet, remove with slotted spoon and set aside.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter baking dish.
Combine all ingredients in dish.
Bake for 3 hours, stirring once during baking.
Add raisins, if desired.

title: people chow
directions: In large bowl, pour in cereal.
In separate bowl, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir until blended.
Pour over cereal.
Add 1 box powdered sugar; place lid on bowl and shake well.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water.
Cook in double boiler or microwave until thick.
Add egg yolks and cook until real thick.
Add lemon juice and rind; stir.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Put in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar and cream of tartar until stiff.
Put on filling and brown in oven.

title: baked apricots
directions: In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer apricots, sugar and crumbs until all ingredients are used.
Pour melted butter over all. Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: kim's chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate wings for 24 hours. Spray baking pan with Pam; bake as 1 layer at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, turning once.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Chop onion, bell pepper and carrots. Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: turkette
directions: Break spaghetti into small pieces (2 to 3 inches long) and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: conch fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough milk for the mixture to hold its shape.
Form into fritters and fry in 350° oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels and serve with hot sauce or the sauce of your choice.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In a large box mix instant pudding, sour cream, milk and orange peel.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, 1 to 2 minutes.
By hand fold in Cool Whip.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan.
Add first 5 ingredients.
Saute until vegetables soften, about 5 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients and saute until fragrant, about 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth. Bring to a boil and cook over medium-high heat until thickens, about 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are opaque, about 4 minutes.
Season with freshly ground black pepper.
Spoon over 3/4 cup rice and garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks with shortening and butter until well blended. Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Add extracts; beat on low speed until blended at low speed. Add flour, about 1/4 at a time, alternating with about 1/3 milk at a time. Add coconut. Mix well. Fold in beaten (stiffly beaten) egg whites. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° about 2 hours. Cool on rack 10 or 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, margarine and cocoa.
Beat in 1 egg at a time; beat well.
Add milk and flour (sifted with baking powder) alternately with milk.
Beat until well mixed.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Ice cake with chocolate icing.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well and set aside.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Add sugar.
Add flour mixture until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in apples and chopped nuts. Spread into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Transfer to a wire cooling rack, cool completely.
(Cake can be frozen up to 3 months.)

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat 6 egg whites with 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar until soft mounds form.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Combine egg yolks, cold water, vanilla and lemon.
Blend egg yolk mixture with dry ingredients.
Beat 1 minute.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg white mix (1/4 at a time).
Do not stir.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Cut through batter to remove bubbles.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Invert pan and leave until cool.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and concentrate.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in oranges.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: deep-fried turkey
directions: Heat peanut oil in King Turkey Cooker to 350°.
Season outside of turkey.
Secure turkey to hangers and submerge into oil.
Cook 8 minutes per pound.
This is the best turkey you will ever have.
Meat is moist and juicy; skin is crispy.
Delicious.

title: dudley's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and drink until creamy.
Add red food coloring and cool.
Combine with fresh whole strawberries.
Pour into cooked crust with a little sugar in bottom.
Add whipped cream.

title: crock-pot special
directions: Combine onion and ground chuck or hamburger in skillet.
Brown and drain.
In 5-quart crock-pot, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook on slow about 4 hours. Serve with corn bread.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Preheat oil in an electric skillet.
Mix all ingredients, then pour batter in
a small funnel a little at a time.
If the batter is too thick, add more milk.
When pouring batter in the oil, make a circle with the batter and crisscross it back and forth.
When the cake is brown on one side, turn and fry the second side until brown.
Remove the cake and place it on a paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered or brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into lightly greased loaf pan. Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: good salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups of water instead of 4.
Add the cottage cheese and other ingredients.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise on top.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Prepare noodles according to directions given on package. Brown beef separately.
Place ground beef, cooked noodles and cans of soup and corn in approximately 2-quart casserole dish. Crush crackers into crumbs.
Place on top after all contents are thoroughly mixed.
Place in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
You can add garlic salt and/or Tabasco sauce to ground beef while browning for a spicier dish.

title: excellent but easy casserole
directions: Combine soups, chilies and tortillas and let soak 30 minutes. Place half of soup mixture in shallow 5-quart casserole.
Cover with chicken.
Add layer of remaining soup mixture and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icing for coconut cake
directions: Heat milk and flour on medium heat until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar until no granulars.
When milk and flour mixture cools, add to creamed mixture and beat until fluffy; add vanilla.
Cover yellow cake mix with icing and sprinkle with coconut.

title: fresh fruit tray orange creme dip
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Serve chilled with fresh fruit. I like orange sections and apple slices plus other fresh fruit.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Place into a crock-pot and melt down or place in a microwave-safe bowl until melted.
Stir as needed.

title: shrimp and feta salad
directions: Combine shrimp, Feta cheese, cottage cheese, onions, tomatoes, oregano and pepper in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add pasta and herbed dressing; toss.
Serve cold.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Melt margarine and add bread, broken up.
Then add remaining ingredients together and pour over bread.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Use 8 x 12-inch pan.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In large casserole, mix together the tuna, peas, noodles, soup, salt and pepper.
Add cheese package from macaroni and cheese box.
Add milk; mix thoroughly.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, or heat in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with salad for a complete meal.

title: jumbalaija
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Cook sausage in drippings.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Repeat with ham and vegetables.
Mix together and add seasonings.
Add broth and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and add rice.
Bake, covered, one hour until liquid is absorbed.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg in a large bowl.
Add chopped onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour uncooked rice into a deep baking dish.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Sprinkle 1/2 of Lipton soup mix on this.
Mix mushroom soup and water in a large bowl, stirring and mixing well.
Then, pour soup over pork chops. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 of Lipton mix over this.
Cover with foil. Bake for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon brown sugar oatmeal
directions: Combine all ingredients for 1 serving in microwave-safe bowl. Cook on High power for 2 minutes until thickened, stirring after every minute of cooking.
Old fashioned oats may take longer. Cover and let stand 2 to 3 minutes before serving.

title: mole salad dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and chill in refrigerator.
Serve on crisp greens; top with grated Romano cheese and toasted sesame seed.

title: egg souffle
directions: Cut off the crust and cube the bread.
Layer the bread cubes, ham and cheese in an 8 x 8-inch glass, greased baking dish.
Whip with spoon, the eggs, milk and salt.
Pour this over the bread mixtures and top with the melted oleo.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
This can be doubled and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the hot water.
Add the marshmallows and stir until dissolved. Cool until almost jelled. Add the cabbage, pineapple (with juice) and nuts.
Mix the salad dressing in the Cool Whip or Dream Whip. Add this to the first mixture.

title: sliced hen with ginger (tyukvetrece)(serves 6)
directions: Rub the chicken breasts with marjoram and ginger.
Then slice them thinly.
Heat oil in a frying pan and saute the onions until glossy.
Add the carrots and brown them slightly.
Add the sliced chicken and saute until the pan juices are reduced by half.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box and put in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over broccoli. Sprinkle a generous amount of dressing crumbs over casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 cup margarine, stir in 1/4 cup cocoa then water.
Bring to boil, remove from heat.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1/3 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until done.
In small saucepan, melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and Eagle Brand.
Stir in confectioners sugar and nuts.
Spread on warm cake.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans until tender. Brown onions and peppers in butter. Mix with lima beans (make sure beans have been drained). Place in greased dish, cover with cheese and crumbled crackers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: perfect brisket
directions: Place brisket in large pan.
Pour liquid smoke over it. Season well with salts and onion.
Cover with foil and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: beans and hot dogs
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: tuna patties
directions: Fry in a skillet until brown and stays together.
Tastes like fried chicken.

title: rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar and let set for 5 minutes.
Add salt, eggs and melted margarine.
Add flour until it is sticky. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, make into rolls. Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Then bake at 400° until brown.

title: bologna ii
directions: Take chicken broth and make gravy to pour over top.
Mix chicken and
vegetables
together.
Put
half
of mixture in greased casserole. Cover with
1/2 pints toasted bread crumbs. Add the rest of mixture and top
with
another
1 1/2 pints bread crumbs.
Pour gravy over top. Be sure to have plenty gravy.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: cheese biscuits with sausage
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crock-pot braised ribs with vegetables
directions: Preheat ribs in skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Put short ribs into pot.
Add tomatoes or juice, salt, pepper, potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cover; simmer at medium setting for 4 to 5 hours or low setting for 7 to 10 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; add sugar gradually and beat until thick.
Add pudding and beat.
Fold in whipped topping, milk and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream freezer can.
Add milk to fill. Freeze ice cream according to your freezer.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until soft enough to mash.
Add brown sugar, crushed pineapple and 2/3 of marshmallows.
Mash together. Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining marshmallows on top.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated through and marshmallows on top are softened and nicely browned.

title: brown sugar pecan rounds
directions: Preheat oven to to 350°.
Mix butter, brown sugar and egg. Stir in flour and pecans.
Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Dough will flatten and spread. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until set.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine hash browns, 3/4 cup butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese in a casserole dish.
Place crushed cornflakes on top of dish.
Use 1/2 cup of butter to soften cornflakes.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes, depending on stove.

title: best ever pear cobbler
directions: Arrange pear slices evenly in a 10 x 6 x 2 inch baking dish; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt; stir well, and sprinkle over pears.
Dot with butter.
Roll pastry to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface;
cut into 10 x 1/2-inch strips.
Arrange in lattice fashion over pears; trim edges.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: coffee cake
directions: Add sugar to milk, yeast and 1 teaspoon salt; mix well.
Add eggs to milk mixture and mix well.
Add this to flour mixture. Put in greased bowl in refrigerator overnight.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix preceding ingredients together and bake in 3 greased and floured layer pans at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoons into pan with oil and fry until browned.

title: bro. rayl's apple bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, cinnamon and eggs with apples.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder; then add it to your apple mixture.
Grease muffin tins or loaf pans.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and stem mushrooms and set on paper towels to drain.
Mix remaining ingredients well (except cheese or paprika) in small mixing bowl.
Use to stuff mushroom caps.

Place in buttered glass baking dish and sprinkle with either Parmesan cheese or paprika. Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly. May microwave on High for 5 minutes, turning after 2 1/2 minutes cooking time.
Serve immediately.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: goforth's chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice and water in a heavy 2 to 3-quart cooking container.
Bring to hard boil in uncovered container.
Lower heat and cover with tight fitting lid.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not remove lid or stir rice while cooking! While rice is cooking, heat oil in large skillet.
Cut chicken into short, thin strips and stir-fry in oil until done.
When rice is done, add chicken, margarine, salt and pepper, gently stirring to combine.
Serve with tossed salad and cantaloupe.
This is one of our family's favorite dishes.
Serves 6.

title: crock-pot steak soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot except flour and butter. Cover and cook on low 8 hours.
One hour before serving turn on high.
Make a paste of butter and flour.
Pour into soup and stir until thick.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients; heat until cheese is melted.

title: mama's cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cut up one head of cabbage. Season as desired and boil until tender. Drain cabbage and place in a casserole dish. Place several pats of butter (as much as desired) all around in the cabbage. Cut Velveeta cheese into slices and place over the cabbage in the casserole dish. Bake in oven until cheese melts and is bubbly. Remove casserole from the oven. Crush enough Town House crackers to cover the entire casserole and melt enough butter to moisten the crushed crackers. Mix together and cover the casserole. Return to the oven and bake until the crust is browned.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in applesauce.
Cool slightly. Stir and pour into mold or dish. Chill.

title: chafing dish beer balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form small bite-size meatballs. Brown balls, then remove from skillet.
Stir tomato paste into drippings.
Add beer to this mixture.
Return meatballs to sauce. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
A pinch of dill seed may be added to the sauce.
Serves 20 to 30.
Keep warm in chafing dish and serve with toothpicks.
(This freezes well.)

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings, gradually adding flour to mixture.
Place in a tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and cinnamon with oleo and pat 1/2 of mixture in bottom of pan.
Spread rhubarb over it.
Cook until thick
the water, sugar, vanilla and cornstarch and pour over rhubarb.
Spread remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Stir well.
Place over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves, then cook to soft ball stage (approximately 232°).
Remove from heat. Add nuts, stirring until well coated.
Spread nuts on waxed paper and separate with a fork.
Cool.
Yields 2 cups.

title: rivels
directions: Mix together into coarse crumbs.
Drop into boiling soup or stew.
Reduce heat and cook approximately 10 minutes.

title: chocolate-nut cookies
directions: In
a mixing bowl, beat cake mix and sour cream with an electric
mixer
on
medium
to
high speed about 2 minutes or until
smooth and creamy, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Stir
in
peanut
butter
pieces or chocolate pieces and nuts. Drop dough from a rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart on a greased cookie
sheet.
Bake
in
a
350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until
tops
look
dry.
Cool
on
cookie
sheet for 1 minute. Remove cookie and cool on wire rack.
Makes about 36.

title: melon ball salad
directions: Combine water, sugar and cinnamon sticks.
Boil 5 minutes, then let cool.
Pour over melon balls; let marinate 1-2 hours before serving.

title: clinton's recipe
directions: Shred chicken (add to sauteed onions and green chilies).
Add Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
Mix well; cook over low heat until all is mixed together and melted.
Warm tortillas in skillet and wrap mixture.
Put in baking pan.
Pour bottle of chili sauce over.
Bake at 250° until warm clear through and sauce looks dry, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: french coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and sour cream.
Mix in dry ingredients except coconut.
Grease 8-inch tube pan or square pan. Line bottom of pan with all the coconut and pour in batter. Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon hot dish
directions: In medium saucepan, combine carrots, celery, onions, water and salt.
Bring to boil, covered, for 15 minutes or until tender. Drain liquid into 2 cup measure.
Place vegetables in serving dish.
Cover to keep warm.
Using saucepan, melt margarine and blend in flour.
Use salmon liquid and vegetable liquid and enough milk to make 2 cups.
Stir into flour mixture.
Cook over medium heat.
Add cheese and Worcestershire sauce until thickened.
Pour over vegetables and salmon.
Serve over baking powder biscuits or mashed potatoes.

title: martha washington cherries
directions: Take a pinch of dough mixture and roll half of cherry in it. Chill well; overnight preferred.

title: cold nachos
directions: Put salsa in a bowl in the middle of the tray.
Cut; shred and chop all ingredients.
Place tortilla on the tray (one layer). Put a teaspoon of refried beans on each chip followed by a teaspoon of sour cream.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over chips. Sprinkle onion, lettuce, tomato and olives.
Serve as is.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Combine celery and onion in a 1-quart microwave dish.
Cover and cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Cover and microwave on High 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring once. Sprinkle with noodles.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until noodles are heated.

title: blackberry ice cream supreme
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Stir in 1 pint vanilla ice cream by spoonfuls until smooth. Chill if necessary until slightly thickened.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: champagne punch
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar is dissolved. Cool. Add the fruit concentrates. Stir well. Add 7-Up.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: peanut butter burst cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.

title: chicken and sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with vegetable spray.
Place chicken pieces in baking dish without overlapping pieces.
Peel sweet potatoes and slice in half inch slices.
Place on and around chicken pieces.

title: favorite white bread
directions: My favorite bread recipe.
Turns out the best homemade bread.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix in soup and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place in small casserole.
Bake at 350°
until bubbly. Top with onion rings.
Garnish with a little chopped pimento. Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Mix and pour in 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake for 35 minutes
at
350°.	Allow to cool 15 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve with crackers.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in Pyrex dish; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soup and water on top of chicken, then add cheese.
Melt oleo; mix with corn bread mix.
Spread this on top of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mystery dip
directions: Shred dried beef into small pieces and mix with other ingredients.
Serve in a small bowl surrounded with chip and crackers to dip with.

title: three greens salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; toss well. Combine vinegar, broth and oil; stir well with a whisk. Pour over pasta mixture; toss gently to coat. Sprinkle with parsley and cheese. Serves 6.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven until mixture is set.

title: delicious fresh orange cake
directions: A nut-sprinkled cream cheese icing is the perfect foil for this moist, not-too-sweet carrot cake.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Boil 2 minutes.
Take off stove.
Stir in 2 cups nuts. Pour out on oil paper and break apart.

title: venison casserole
directions: Put roast in crock-pot.
Pour sauce over meat.
Do not add water.
Cook on low overnight or all day.

title: spiced bran drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine brown sugar, butter, shortening, coffee and egg. Beat until light and fluffy. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove immediately.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put beef in blender.
Mix half the beef and remaining ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.
Shape as desired and roll in 1/2 of dried beef.
Decorate with celery, onions and lettuce, if desired.

title: calamari salad (italian)(octopus, english; pulpo, spanish)
directions: Put 3 cans octopus with oil into bowl.
Squeeze 3 lemons into bowl.
Eliminate pits by squeezing through strainer.
Thinly slice onion and pepper.
Add onion, pepper and crushed garlic.
Add olive oil and 1/4 cup red wine vinegar.
Mix together.
Cover the bowl and refrigerate.
Serve with Italian bread or just by itself.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Dice large eggplant.
Chop a little onion.
Cook in salt water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add milk, mushroom soup, egg and 1 cup stuffing.
Put in greased casserole.
Put 1/2 cup herb stuffing on top along with melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat, low cholesterol chocolate chip cookies that really taste
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese, then combine in mixing bowl.
Add sugars and beat thoroughly.
Add vanilla, butter flavor and Egg Beaters.
Mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking soda; stir these together with a fork.
Add flour mixture to dough a little at a time.
After all the flour is mixed in, add the mini morsels.
The little chips go a long way.
Spray cookie pan with nonstick spray and drop dough onto pan in rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.

title: mushroom crust quiche
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add mushrooms and cook until limp.
Stir in crackers, then turn mixture into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Press mixture evenly over pan bottom and up the sides.
In the same frying pan, melt remaining 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add onion and cook until limp.
Spread onion over mushroom crust; sprinkle evenly with cheese.

title: chicken and squash casserole
directions: Mix oleo with stuffing mix.
Put half of this mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix all other ingredients and place in pan on mixture.
Add the rest of the stuffing mix to top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together; pour into 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: margie's flaky fried pastry
directions: The secret of sourdough is in the aging process that occurs between uses.
Your starter will last for a long time and give you much enjoyment, but do not let it just sit in the refrigerator too long without using.

title: summer slush
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well to mix.
Pour into containers suitable for freezing, but large enough to scoop from.
Stir once or twice after placing in freezer until mixture is firm.
To serve, scoop into glasses and add Sprite, 7-Up or ginger ale.
Refreshing in summer, winter, spring and fall.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix cream and eggs and allow to stand in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to prepare, remove from refrigerator. Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook sausage until done; drain and crumble. Trim crust from bread slices.
Place them in the bottom of the pan.
Place the crumbled sausage over the bread.
Add the grated cheese.
Pour the egg mixture over the top of the other ingredients.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix well the rice, milk and sugar.
Dot top with butter and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine; mix well.
Press 1/2 the cake mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle nuts and chips over cake.
Pour melted caramels over this.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mix, pressing gently into caramel.
Add remaining nuts, pressing gently.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: orange sherbet fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet and mix until sherbet is dissolved.
Let partially set in refrigerator and then add whipped cream.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding as box instructs, then add pumpkin and Cool Whip and spices.
Spread into 9-inch graham cracker crust or regular pie shell.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and peppers.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with a little water and add to sauce mixture.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown beef in butter. Remove from heat.
Put tomato sauce in meat; stir.
May use a dash of salt and sprinkle of sugar.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
Spread half-cooked noodles onto greased dish.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Put in the remaining noodles.
Pour melted butter over noodles.
Put ground beef and tomato sauce on top.
I sprinkle a little cheese on top.

title: beef and vegetable kebabs
directions: Cut the green pepper in half.
Remove and discard the core and seeds.
Cut the pepper flesh into 1-inch pieces with a sharp knife.

title: applesauce and oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cup oats, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Add applesauce, skim milk, 1/2 cup brown sugar, oil and egg white.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Combine 1 tablespoon brown sugar, the 1/4 cup oats, 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle over unbaked muffins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: sour cream burgers
directions: Thoroughly combine ground beef, sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, onions and salt.
Crush corn flakes slightly, gently stir into meat mixture.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Shape into 6 patties, about 1/2-inch thick.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 6 minutes, turn and broil 6 minutes longer or until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise with artichokes and garlic.
Mix 1/2 the cheeses into artichoke mix.
Put into a casserole dish.
On top, add remaining cheeses.
Add little pats of butter on top.

title: black walnut icing for 4 cake layers
directions: Cook slowly, 1 hour, until thick.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put icing on hot cake layers.
Then sprinkle nuts over filling.

title: broccoli - ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill and serve.

title: whole wheat cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat
water
to
boiling.
Add	oil and honey.	Stir in gluten,
yeast,
salt
and	enough fresh ground wheat flour to make
sticky (about 7 cups).
Knead well; let rise.
Roll part into
rectangle and spread with filling and raisins.
Roll up, cut into rolls and bake at 350°.
Ice when cool (if desired).

title: applesauce cookies(this cookie recipe calls for applesauce.)
directions: In a bowl, cream shortening with sugar.
In a separate bowl, sift dry ingredients, then add to creamed mixture alternately with the applesauce.
Drop with a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 2 plus 2 plus 2
directions: Layer meat, onions and soup in crock-pot.
Cook 8 to 10 hours on low.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix all ingredients, except celery.
Put mixture into celery and enjoy.

title: new year's cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften and mix all ingredients (except pecans). Roll into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Recipe makes 2 large balls or 1 extra large ball or log.

title: feather scones
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt, then rub in the shortening.
Beat eggs and milk together, then stir in.
Use a bit more milk if necessary to make a rather soft yet easily handled dough.
Turn out on a floured board and knead slightly. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into a triangle with knife or cut with a round cutter.
Place on an ungreased baking pan. Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes or until light and brown. Serve at once with butter.
Makes about 30.

title: light diet burgers
directions: Combine beef, 1-1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper and

2 tablespoons steak sauce. Form into several patties. In large skillet, sear patties on both sides. Remove from pan; lower heat and add onions, peppers, mushrooms, 2 tablespoons steak sauce and 1 teaspoon salt. Simmer until vegetables are tender. Replace patties. Simmer until meat is cooked. Add tomatoes at the end, just to heat through.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry bacon, reserve drippings.
Add sugar and vinegar to drippings and simmer until clear.
Drain beans, reserve 1/2 cup liquid.

title: pineapple and cream cheese cake
directions: Mix and bake cake at 325°
in 3 layers.

title: nippy pork chop platter
directions: Spread mustard over pork chops.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in bag.
Shake chops in bag to coat.
Then, brown in heavy skillet in melted fat.
Place chops in baking dish; cover with soup and milk that has been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together the green beans, Shoe Peg corn, celery soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and chopped onion.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with margarine.
Pour on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until brown; drain drippings.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 8-inch or 10 x 10-inch pan.
Top with cheese; spoon beans over cheese.
Prepare corn bread as directed on package; pour on top. Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes, or until corn bread is brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, and sugar; set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Add mayonnaise mixture; mix well. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: knipfla soup
directions: Boil potatoes.
Add bay leaves, allspice and onion.
Boil until potatoes are half done, about 1/2 hour.
Use enough water as it is used for the soup broth.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni 6 minutes and drain.
In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add elbows.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake the cake in 2 (8-inch) cake pans.
When cool, make 4 layers, then frost with 12 Minute Icing in between layers and on top and sides.
Ice with chocolate icing.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup water
or more to moisten.
Drop teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until sausage is cooked.

title: broccoli orange salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Add mayonnaise mixture to the broccoli mixture.
Gently stir in oranges.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix cake per box instructions.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake per instructions.
Let cool slightly.
With a wooden spoon handle, poke holes in cake at 2-inch intervals.
Drizzle topping over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over topping.
Sprinkle Heath bars over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: four-bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain all beans.
Combine with pepper and onions. Blend remaining ingredients together well to dissolve sugar.
Pour over bean mixture.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Throw all together in a bowl and stir until mixed.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; pack in pint jars. Have a shallow pan of hot water ready. Turn jars upside down in pan. This allows steam to rise in jars and heat cucumbers. Do not leave too long. Heat, but do not boil, vinegar, water, sugar, and salt; remove jars and pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers. Let set for several weeks before opening jars to eat. Good with fish!

title: german slaw
directions: Pour 1 cup sugar over shredded vegetables and peppers; mix and set aside.
Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate from 12 to 24 hours in a covered container.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: canned green peanuts
directions: Wash peanuts. Put in large pan and bring to a boil.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix soups and sour cream together with meat; pour in greased casserole dish.
Put crackers in Zip Lock bag and pour melted margarine and shake well; pour over top of casserole and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake in 350° oven until good and hot.

title: broccoli with bacon and chestnuts
directions: Cut the broccoli into florets, peel the stems and cut into 1/4 inch thick slices. In a heavy skillet, cook the bacon until crisp. Remove from the pan and drain all but 1 Tbsp. fat.
