Add the olive oil and butter, heat until bubbly. Add the chestnuts and saut for 1 minute. Add the bacon and hold on low heat. Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add the broccoli and time for 5 minutes or until done to the desired tenderness. Drain well and put back into hot pan. Add the bacon-chestnut mixture to the broccoli; salt and pepper, toss and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Be sure it's beginning to thicken.
If doubled, it takes longer to cook.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice boiled potatoes.
Fry bacon slowly, drain on paper.
Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Carefully stir in potatoes and crumbled bacon bits.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand until ready to serve, 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable bar
directions: Press crescent rolls on a large flat cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons of sugar and put in a flat baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Bake 8 minutes in a 400° oven. Remove and pat down; cool.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper pork pieces and brown quickly.
Place rice in bottom of large buttered baking dish and cover with orange juice. Put pork pieces on top of rice and pour can of soup over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check if additional moisture is needed.
Replace with orange juice or water.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until done.

title: big art's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat for 20 minutes. Turn off and let simmer.
Now get ready for the best barbecue sauce you have ever tasted.

title: scottish minches
directions: Brown
beef
in
vegetable
oil, then pour off any fat. Add onion
and garlic to meat; steam together 10 minutes.
Add potato, seasonings
and
water to cover potato.
Simmer until potato
is mushy.
Pour
into	baking	dish; top with crumbs. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to boil; boil 1 minute.
Add Jell-O.
Let cool.
Put in pie crust.

title: my own pizza
directions: Lay two biscuits side by side and press out into a circular form.
Place flattened biscuits on greased cookie sheets.
Top with sauce and desired toppings.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients and pour over spareribs. Put in crock-pot on low for 8 hours.
You can also put in oven for 3 hours at 350°.

title: meat loaf festiva
directions: Mix in	all
ingredients
by
hand, except catsup, in a large bowl.
Work
the
mixture into a large ball.
Divide the ball into 4	portions.
Press
each portion into a Bundt cake pan.
Place the
cake pan on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 315° for 1 1/2 hours. Drain
any fat every 1/2 hour.
Cool 15 minutes. Turn the meat loaf onto serving dish.
Garnish with catsup.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble 1 to 1 1/2 cups of cornbread into a big salad bowl.
In another bowl combine tomatoes, pepper, onion, pickle and bacon. Spoon half the vegetable mixture over the cornbread.
Stir together the mayo and pickle juice in a small bowl.
Repeat the layering with the remaining cornbread, vegetable and dressing.
Garnish as desired.
Cover tightly and chill 2-3 hours before serving.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: chicken or veal marsala
directions: In a large frying pan, put olive oil and garlic; brown.
Pound chicken breasts or veal until 1/4-inch thickness.
Add breading which you have added:
salt, pepper, oregano, thyme, basil and marjoram.
Add chicken to oil; saute until lightly browned, about 2 minutes on each side, then add sliced mushrooms and cook until browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup Marsala wine and the Rhine wine; bring to a boil.
Add tomatoes and a little sugar; season to your taste.
Let simmer, covered, while you boil water and cook your fettucine noodles.
When noodles are cooked, toss with margarine and grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve with chicken or veal sauce.
Bon appetit to you.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Flatten and sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up and form into a loaf.
Top with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pan; blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and heat until melted.
Place drained potatoes in a baking dish; cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: appleless apple pie
directions: Bring sugar, water and cream of tartar to a boil.
Add crackers.
Boil for 2 minutes; cool.
Pour into a pie shell. Sprinkle with spice.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook a few minutes to saute the vegetables.
Add other ingredients and pour into a large casserole.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 12 to 16.

title: ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream of celery soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Layer other ingredients. Pour soup/milk mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Place butter in bowl.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add bananas and buttermilk.
Mix until moistened and beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs and beat 2 minutes longer.
If desired, fold in walnuts. Bake in 2 greased and floured 9 x 9 pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: eggplant-tomato casserole
directions: Cover eggplant with salted water and boil for 10 minutes.
In buttered baking dish, layer the eggplant, corn and tomatoes. Sprinkle with sugar, bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: kappa alpha theta casserole
directions: Cut crusts off of bread and cut into cubes.
Cook celery until tender. Put 1/2 of bread cubes in bottom of 3-quart casserole. Mix shrimp, crabmeat, green pepper, diced celery, salt and mayonnaise and spread over bread.
Mix egg, milk and mustard and pour over mixture in casserole.
Cover with rest of bread.
Spread over the top one can of undiluted cream of mushroom soup.
Spread cheese over top and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred the Cheddar cheese and let stand until softened.
Cream together with softened cream cheese.
Add chopped red pepper, chopped green pepper, garlic and hot pepper.
(Drain off excess juice before adding to cheese.)
Add smidgen Italian seasoning, parsley and oregano.
Add couple drops Worcestershire sauce.
Blend with mixer.
Shape on plate and refrigerate.
Seasonings are really to your own liking.
There is no exact measurement.
Don't worry, you'll get better with practice.

title: caramel raisin pie
directions: Line pan with uncooked crust.
Sprinkle raisins in crust.
Mix sugar, flour and whipping cream.
Pour over raisins and cover with top crust.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
If edges brown too fast, cover with foil and continue cooking.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make in large punch bowl.
Bake brownies as directed on box. After baking brownies, pour Kahlua over the top and let soak (optional, it is just as good without it).
Cut brownies in chunks and place half in bottom of punch bowl.
Sprinkle half of chopped Skor bars, spread half of the mousse and next the Cool Whip. Repeat.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.
Serves a lot.

title: pecan pie 2
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add nuts. Pour in two shells (uncooked) and bake 45 minutes on 350°.

title: tender barbecue ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make a marinade.
Add marinade to large Dutch oven with 5 to 6 pounds spareribs (I like country style ribs).
Simmer on stove approximately 1 hour, stirring occasionally to make sure all ribs are covered.
Place the "cooked" ribs on hot barbecue grill to sear.
Serve and enjoy. Pass around the cooked marinade and use as barbecue sauce.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: down home barbecue sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat all ingredients to boiling. Reduce heat to a low temperature. Simmer for 10 minutes. Makes 1 3/4 cups of sauce. Pour over your cooked meat dish.

title: lemon delight
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in 1 cup topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Saute bacon.
Add potatoes, onion, marjoram and beef stock. Cook 25 minutes.
Add leeks, carrots and celery.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cream.
Cook 5 minutes.
Season.
Garnish with parsley.

title: buttermilk pie #2
directions: Cream butter and sugar until it looks grainy, then add flour and eggs until it looks creamy.
Fold in buttermilk, butter flavoring, lemon extract and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Check at 30 minutes, if getting too brown, cut down 25 degrees.) Done when middle is not wiggly.

title: magic french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chips over boiling water.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Place slice of ham and swiss cheese on each chicken breast.
Tuck in and roll up like a jelly roll. Combine crumbs, parmesan and parsley.
In baking dish, melt butter on high for 30 - 40 seconds.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in crumbs.
Arrange chicken rolls seam side down.
Cook, covered at 70 percent power in microwave for 12 - 15 minutes until done. Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for 3 hours.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Sprinkle meat with meat tenderizer. Pound meat to tenderize and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Heat oil in Dutch oven or large pot.
Brown meat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low for 2 hours.
Stir frequently and add more water if necessary.
Combine cornstarch with small amount of water and mix well.
Add to stew and cook to thicken.
Serve with cornbread.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, granulated sugar and oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 8 minutes at 325°; cool.

title: catherine's southwest cheesecake
directions: Combine cheeses until creamy.
Add eggs, taco seasoning and chilies.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove from oven and spread sour cream on top.
Return to oven for 5 more minutes.
Cool.
Then refrigerate overnight.
When serving, remove sides.
Pour a jar of salsa on top.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except carrots, together.
After well mixed, add carrots.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer pans for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Use Carrot Cake Icing.

title: caramel rum fondue
directions: Heat caramels, rum extract, butter and water in a double-boiler over moderate heat, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Pour into fondue pot and keep warm.
Spear apple slices and dip in fondue.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, garlic and onions (until onions are limp) in artichoke marinade.
Stir in drained and dry spinach, soup and sour cream, eggs, oregano, nutmeg, pepper and lemon juice until well blended.

title: cobbler dessert
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Work like pie dough.
Mix together eggs and vanilla, then add to dough.
If dough is stiff, add up to 2 tablespoons milk.
Divide dough in half and press 1/2 into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put filling over bottom.
Flatten pieces of remaining dough and place on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Frizzle meat.
Add onions and garlic.
Add other ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Cut into small or 2-inch lengths.
Add to meat mixture. Layer this with cheese, two layers each.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, flour and orange juice.
Cook until thick and while hot add marshmallows and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add drained pineapple and mandarin oranges.
When cold, fold in whipped cream.
Sprinkle ground nuts on top (optional). Let stand overnight.

title: easy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in buttered 1-quart casserole. Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake cake.
Split each layer in half to make 4 layers.
Beat Cool Whip into coconut mixture.
Frost layers and refrigerate.

title: steak diane
directions: Sprinkle steaks with pepper and salt. In a skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of margarine, stir in onions and mustard. Cook for 1 minute. Add steaks, cook for 3 minutes on each side or until meat reaches desired doneness. Remove to serving plate and keep warm. Add lemon juice, worcestershire sauce and remaining butter to skillet. Cook for 2 minutes. Add parsley and chives. Pour over steaks.

title: layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of bowl.
Cover with celery and onion.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Cover with thick layer of cheese.
Sprinkle bacon on the top.
Let sit one hour before tossing.

title: easy no bake banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk (beat).
Fold in Cool Whip and condensed milk.
Layer bananas and wafers.
Put pudding mixture on top. Refrigerate.

title: holiday house fragrance
directions: Simmer all ingredients. Add more as needed. Smell and Enjoy!!!

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pastry shell. Cook in oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: kansas coffeecake
directions: Crumble sugars, oleo, flour and rolled oats together.
Set back 1 cup for topping.
Mix in eggs, buttermilk, soda and salt. Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle reserved cup of crumbs on top of batter. You may then put mini chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Number of servings:

title: joy's chicken
directions: Wrap 1 strips bacon around rolled half of each chicken breast. Place 8 pieces of chicken in casserole which has been covered with 1 layer of beef.
Mix sour cream and soups.
Pour over chicken.
Do not salt.
Cook, uncovered, 3 hours at 300°.
If you like you may increase sour cream and soup.

title: chewy chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.

In large bowl, stir together butter and cocoa until mixture is smooth. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, eggs, vanilla extract, oats, baking mix, salt, vanilla milk chips and peanut butter chips until well blended.
Let batter rest 10 minutes; drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until tops begin to dry (do not overbake).
Cool 5 minutes; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, then milk and beaten egg. Add water until right consistency.

title: ranch cornbread
directions: Beat buttermilk and egg together slightly.
Sift cornmeal, baking powder, soda and salt together; add to buttermilk and egg mixture.
Pour into a hot 9-inch iron skillet, into which 2 to 3 tablespoons bacon drippings have been melted.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown the meat.
Add the beans, tomatoes, salt, catsup and steak sauce.
Pour mix in baking dish.
Mix the cornbread and drop by tablespoons on top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° until cornbread is brown.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop in well-greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° until brown.
You let biscuits rise in muffin tin from about 20 minutes to around 1 hour before baking.
They are light, puffy and fluffy.

title: basic marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and liquid, spices and sugar.
Cover and simmer over medium heat 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Cool and divide into 3 half-pint freezer containers.
Freeze and use to make Mediterranean Stuffed Potatoes, Southwest Turkey Pie or marinara makes an excellent base for spaghetti sauce.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts (set aside).
Cook rice (set aside). Saute onion, butter and broccoli together.
Add cream of mushroom soup, milk and chicken broth.
Add pieces of Velveeta cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cooked chicken (cubed) and cooked rice. Butter casserole dish and pour all ingredients into it.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes, until top is brown.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: mexican broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Chop onion in small pieces.
Prepare rice according to box directions, but add the chopped onion to the water before it boils.
Steam the broccoli until tender.
Add the steamed broccoli and mushroom soup to the rice; mix together well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: streusel ginger cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well and dust with flour a square pan (9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch).

title: spiced apple pancakes
directions: Make pancakes and serve with sauce.

title: soft bread sticks(for bread machine)
directions: Place yeast, flour, sugar, herbs, oil, water and salt in bread machine pan and process on dough setting.
After cycle is complete, remove dough to lightly floured board and form into a tight ball.
Cover with bread machine pan and let the dough rest for 10 minutes.
Heat over to 350°.
Spritz 2 large baking sheets with cooking spray.
Cut dough into 16 equal size pieces.
Roll each piece into 20-inch long ropes.
Place sticks on prepared baking sheet, sides not touching.
Set aside to rise until puffy (about 15 minutes).
Brush with frothy egg white.
Sprinkle with desired topping.
Bake until golden brown (about 20 to 25 minutes).
Cool on baking sheet for 5 minutes, then remove to rack.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until tests done. Cool.
Spread marshmallow cream over cooled brownies.

title: jello dessert with topping
directions: Let jello jell.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Combine onion, rice and hot broth.
Bring to a boil on top of range.
Cover and cook in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yum yum casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9 x 2 pan with Pam.
Lay 1 can of croissant rolls in bottom of dish.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Spread on croissants.
Top with another can of croissants.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle with mixture over top of margarine.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, hot water mixed with chocolate, then dry ingredients with sour milk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients; heat until butter melts.
Wrap each apple wedge in a section of crescent roll.
Place in baking pan and pour syrup over them.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with a scoop of ice cream, or top with whipped cream.

title: oatmeal bars(20)
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Beat other ingredients well, add the dry ingredients and beat again.
Place in large greased pan (jelly roll type).
Spread over pan.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Ice with "thin" powdered sugar icing.

title: maple cream bonbons
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar and maple flavoring until smooth. Stir in walnuts. Shape into 1-inch balls; place on waxed paper-lined baking sheets. Freeze until firm.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix all five ingredients, then add Cool Whip last. Refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add sugar and syrup.
Stir until dissolved.
Then add peanuts.
Cook over high heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cook 1 minute after first peanut pops.
Do not let brown.
Remove from heat, stir in soda, then pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cook egg noodles in chicken broth.
When noodles are done, drain and add chicken along with other ingredients, except Ritz crackers and butter.
Pour in dish. Spread crackers over top of casserole.
Then pour melted butter on top of cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° about 30 minutes.

title: orange-peach refresher
directions: Peel and pit peaches.
In blender container, combine orange juice, milk powder, ice cubes and fruit.
Cover and blend until the mixture is smooth.
Pour into 2 glasses.
Garnish with additional peach slices and mint sprigs, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with white rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set pan aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters; roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and butter; pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool bread 10 minutes.
Turn onto plate.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt together three times.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Beat well; add milk with soda, then beat in flour and vanilla.
Last, add boiling water.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 3 cups strawberries.
To one cup of sweetened berries, add 1 cup hot water; bring to boiling point and add 1 strawberry jello; stir until completely dissolved.
Cool until beginning to set.
Then stir in remainder of berries, vanilla extract and whipped cream.
(Whip 1/2 pint of whipping cream, and use remainder for top of pie.)
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until filled pie is set and top with rest of whipped cream.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chicken broccoli casserole(small recipe)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients; place in casserole dish and cover with 1 (4 ounce) package shredded American cheese or Cheddar cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple jelly
directions: In an 8 to 10-quart kettle, combine apples and 5 cups of water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until very soft, stirring occasionally.
Strain through a jelly bag or clean pillowcase.
Do not squeeze.
Measure juice.
Add enough water to make 4 cups liquid.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: benne bites
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet (Pam) and preheat oven to 350°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: heavenly ambrosia
directions: Arrange half of the oranges in bottom of bowl; sprinkle with half of the coconut.
Add the pineapple; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Add remaining oranges.
Chill.
Garnish with additional coconut if desired.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix together until spreading consistency.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Bake on cookie sheet in 400° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pot.
When thoroughly mixed, heat and stir until thick.
Cool and knead.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and Jell-O.
Add egg and vanilla. Add flour and soda.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: czechoslovakian cheese cake
directions: Margaret Schultz' mother was born in a Pennsylvania Dutch community.
Her ancestors moved from Holland to Germany so the Dutch Pepernoten became Pfeffernuesse in Germany.
Same recipe, different name.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat over medium heat. Add onion rings and green peppers. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Combine brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, pineapple juice and cornstarch. Heat until smooth. Add can of pineapple and pour over meat mixture. Simmer for 5 minutes. Season to taste. Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with skim milk, then mix with other ingredients.
Put into a graham cracker pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle with chopped pecans or wafer crumbs.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix sugar and butter; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and ginger.
Mix creamed ingredients and dry ingredients with sour cream.
Add raisins last and mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a well-greased loaf pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut cube steak in thin strips and season well with garlic salt, pepper and sprinkle of ginger.
Brown lightly in deep skillet with 1/2 cup oil.
Remove from skillet.
Saute celery slices and pepper strips.
When "crisp-tender" or color has changed, add meat, soy sauce and cornstarch dissolved in water (may add more water as mixture thickens).
Cook about 3 minutes. Add diced tomatoes and salt.
Heat well.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: dairy potato bake
directions: Stir together first 8 ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir until well coated.
Top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: mississippi corn salad
directions: Cut green onions up, including green tips.
Add cut up tomato. Add drained corn.
Mix mayonnaise, yogurt and bay leaf (crushed). Salt and pepper and mix.
Refrigerate 4 to 14 hours.

title: champion sponge cake
directions: Sift together 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites at high speed until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Gradually add 1/2 cup of sugar, beating until stiff but not dry and peaks form.
Combine egg yolks, water, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Beat at medium-high speed until thick and lemon colored (about 4 minutes).
Gradually fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Invert to cool.
Serve plain or frost with Pineapple Frosting.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in butter.
Add mushrooms, flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Cook until thick and hot.

title: scotch chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in
a bowl and mix well.
In a saucepan, mix butter, shortening, cocoa and water. Bring to a rapid bowl.
Pour over flour and sugar, mixing gradually.
Add soda with buttermilk and add to other ingredients.
Mix together and pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make icing 5 minutes before cake is done and pour over hot cake.

title: pork chops with apple
directions: In shallow dish, combine apple and lemon juice, onion and savory.
Add pork chops, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Remove chops and place on broiler pan.
Strain marinade and set aside.
Bake chops at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg, sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla extract, beating thoroughly. Pour into glass and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Combine the sugars and sour cream in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly. Continue cooking this mixture without stirring until it reaches 238° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until nuts are thickly covered and the coating loses its gloss.
(Don't give up, this takes a while!)
Spoon nuts onto wax paper and separate nuts with forks.
Cool completely before storing in an airtight container.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion & pepper in cooking oil. Add hamburger meat and cook until done. Drain grease, and stir in soup and noodles. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.

title: double chocolate-mint chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In top of double boiler, melt 3/4 cup morsels over hot (not boiling) water; stir until smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In large bowl, beat butter, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Add melted morsels and egg; beat well. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Allow to stand for 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet; cool completely before covering.
Yield:
1 1/2 dozen.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Then blend in egg; add other ingredients to mixture.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Roll dough into 1/8 inch thickness.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in preheated moderate oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 dozen cookies about 2 inches in diameter.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla; put nuts in the bottom of pie crust and pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done or bake at 400° for 30 minutes with pie pan on top, then take off pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Unroll, don't separate 1 package crescent rolls and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread on the cheese mixture.
Brush top with beaten egg yolk. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 24 to 30.

title: strawberry pie - baked graham cracker crust
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir Jell-O about 3 minutes; add 2 cups ice cubes.
Stir until ice melts and Jell-O thickens.
Blend Cool Whip into Jell-O until smooth.
Fold in strawberries.
Chill until mixture will mound.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: golden glow
directions: In large pitcher or punch bowl, combine concentrates and water. Just before serving, add ginger ale and ice; stir to blend. Makes 25 (4 oz.) servings.

title: mini chip sour cream streusel cake
directions: In saucepan, heat sugar and water to boiling.
Remove and add chips; stir until melted and desired consistency.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients to the stage you can test with finger without burning.
Beat eggs and the first mixture and beat to mix.
Add yeast.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Beat until dough is smooth.
If dough seems too thin, add additional flour until dough climbs up the beaters.
Set bowl in warm water; let rise until double in bulk.
Turn on greased baking sheet.
Let rise for 20 to 30 minutes in a warm place.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 20 to 24 rolls.

title: lemon salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O with 1 cup hot water.
Cream in cream cheese slightly.
Let this set, then fold in cottage cheese, celery, nuts and pineapple.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer in order.
Serve cold with chips.

title: potato pancakes
directions: First, shred potatoes in a food processor or on a cheese grater.
Place the shredded potatoes in a medium sized bowl and cover with cold water.
Chill in fridge for at least 30 minutes. Drain potatoes, squeeze out the excess moisture with hands.
In a medium bowl, combine the potatoes, eggs, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Heat 2 tbsp. bacon grease in a skillet.
When hot, drop potatoes by spoonfuls and fry until golden brown on both sides. Serve.

title: sunset salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Let cool some.
Then add carrots and pineapple.

title: purple cow
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered shaker and shake until well blended.
Pour in tall glass and slurp!!!

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika in paper or plastic bag.
Brush chicken with lemon juice.
Add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time to bag and shake well to coat chicken with flour mixture.
In 12-inch skillet, brown the chicken slowly in hot shortening. Dissolve bouillon granules in the boiling water.
Stir in green onion, brown sugar, lemon peel and any remaining lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; reduce heat and cook over low heat for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
Combine with butter, grated Parmesan cheese and eggs. Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: grandma's cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix butter, oil, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add the sugar, flour and salt; beat well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture along with eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix corn flakes and melted margarine.
Spread over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salad (dessert or with meal)
directions: Heat Apple sauce until hot enough to dissolve jello. Add orange juice. Refrigerate until firm. Serve squares on lettuce leaf. Suggestion: serve sour cream as dressing.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients and serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: kibbee and eggs
directions: Beat eggs (number of eggs will depend upon the amount of Kibbee and number of people you're serving).
Gently mix in Kibbee and pour into pan and cook like an omelette.
Serve with a cucumber and Laban salad.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice and mix thoroughly.
Pour over rice in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until set.
Sprinkle additional nutmeg on top.

title: pecan delight
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar while beating.
When stiff, fold in pecans, crackers and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cool. Spread whipped topping on pie and keep refrigerated.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in medium bowl.
Add eggs, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Add pecans. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Butter 9 x 13 pan. Put half of this mixture in pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with crackers.
If desired, can add a couple of shakes of hot sauce.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.
Cool completely.

title: creamy onion dip
directions: Blend sour cream, dry onion soup mix, crumbled Blue Cheese and chopped walnuts.
Makes 2 cups.

title: turkey soup
directions: Place turkey carcass in 5-quart pot.
Fill to within 1 1/2-inches from top with water (about 22 cups).
Add bouillon. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove from heat.
Take out turkey carcass.
Let cool.
Remove all meat from carcass.
Put into bowl; cover and refrigerate.
Pour broth into large container and refrigerate.
Next day, heat broth, then add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook until barley and vegetables are cooked.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck; add onion, salt and garlic salt and pepper and simmer until onion is tender.
Drain.
In large boiler, mix Prego, sauce, Ro-Tel and meat.
Simmer for a minimum of 30 minutes.
While sauce is simmering, cook noodles until tender. When noodles are done, add to sauce.
Delicious!
Even better the next day!

title: bran loaf bread
directions: Soften cereal in milk.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir egg and shortening into softened cereal.
Add flour mixture; stir just until all flour is moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 360° for about 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on rack.
For easier cutting, store in refrigerator overnight (wrapped).

title: honey rutabaga
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer mixture 40 to 45 minutes.

title: winter chili sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer slowly for about 1 hour or until thickened.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook sugar, butter, cocoa, nuts and peanut butter.
Boil 1 minute or longer.
Drop on wax paper.

title: goodies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread dry cake mix.
Melt margarine and mix with 1 egg.
Dribble this over dry cake mix.
Press down on bottom of pan.
In another bowl, mix softened cream cheese, 2 eggs and sugar.
Pour over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into small squares.
Very rich!

title: creates it's own crust coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add milk and flour, blending well.
Add coconut.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Boil the white sugar and Karo syrup together for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter, vanilla and cereal. Drop onto waxed paper; let cool.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Trim excess fat from steak; slice across grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Brown steak in oil.
Add onion and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Combine sour cream, soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce and add to steak.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Serve over noodles sprinkled with poppy seed.
Yields 4 servings.

title: tuna tetrazzini(microwave)
directions: Combine cooked spaghetti, soup and milk in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add tuna, mushrooms, onion and 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook on Full power for 8 minutes.
Stir halfway through and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook in Full power for 1 to 2 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir the dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Beat well and bake in an 8-inch greased pan in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet.
Pour off drippings. Add Ragu sauce and mix well while simmering.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs and Mozzarella cheese in bowl.
Mix until smooth. Layer noodles, sauce and cheese mixture alternately in 9 x 13-inch baking dish until ingredients are used.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, at 325° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: steak fingers
directions: For milk, mustard and flour, amounts are approximate.

title: non-fattening potato slices
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potato into thin rounds.
Soak in cold, salted water.
Spread a layer of potato rounds on a lined baking sheet.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Bake without turning for about 1 hour.
Potatoes will brown and puff and will taste almost like French fries.

title: pig lickin' cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box, except don't add water.
Use the juice from oranges.
Add oranges and 3 tablespoons pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream butter and vanilla.
Add 1 tablespoon water and flour. Mix thoroughly; stir in nuts and shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: green rice
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package and set aside.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Add Cheez Whiz while broccoli is hot.
Saute onions, celery and pepper in margarine.
Mix rice and vegetables and add soup.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the reserved butter and corn flakes.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with corn flakes.
Pour reserved butter over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheez whiz soup
directions: Heat and cook all vegetables with juice from the can.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and melt.
Do not let it boil.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together crushed wafers and 1/2 cup margarine and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, 1 cup margarine and 2 cups powdered sugar; beat until fluffy and spread over crust.
Slice bananas (coated with lemon juice) layer over filling.
Drain pineapple, layer over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple, sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Put 1 cherry in center of each serving. Refrigerate.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Combine milk and corn in top of double boiler.
Saute minced onion in butter for a few minutes (do not brown); add flour.
Add to corn mixture and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Mash through a strainer.
Just before serving, add well-beaten egg, cream, chives, parsley, salt and pepper.
Reheat.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Have meat ground twice.
Combine the beef and pork.
Season with the salt and pepper.
Add other ingredients; mix well and shape into a loaf.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: orange ambrosia
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; mix all ingredients together well.
Serve cold.

title: golden salad
directions: Dissolve
jello with hot water in a bowl and cool.
Add other ingredients
and
mix well.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish, congeal. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vanilla; then beat in egg until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Blend in flour.
Refrigerate in a covered bowl overnight or at least 2 1/2 hours.
When ready to cook, spoon out dough on a lightly floured cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: gak
directions: Fill 1 dixie cup 1/3 full of blue starch.
Fill 1 dixie cup 1/3 full of Elmer's glue.
Dump together and mix with index finger until slimy.
Add a drop or two of food coloring.
Store in a Ziploc bag.
This is a toy, not to eat!

title: croatian povetica cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together and add slowly to the creamed mixture.
Put vanilla in the sour cream and stir it in the rest of the mixture.
Then swirl in the nut mixture.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground meat with onions. In a soup pot, combine meat and onions with remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer 45 minutes. Serve with cheese and tortilla chips.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Cream butter and add sifted powdered sugar.
Mix in cinnamon. Put on toast, English muffins, biscuits, etc.

title: valerie's caesar dressing
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a jar and let rest for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Toss with romaine lettuce, croutons, and grated parmesan cheese.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and chicken.
Mix well and put into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix crushed crackers and melted oleo. Cover the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: ryan's cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
(Drain pineapple very good.)
Mix well.
Spoon into small dishes or large bowl.
Chill.

title: olive meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
It will have a red look after cooking due to the tomato sauce.

title: serve on hot dogs
directions: Saute peppers and onion until tender.
Add sauerkraut and heat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Bake in two loaf pans for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Arrange fruit in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup of the sugar over fruit.
Mix the remaining 2/3 cup of sugar with the melted butter, egg and flour and pour over the fruit.
Bake at 325° approximately 45 minutes.

title: date and nut caramel roll
directions: Combine sugar and milk in heavy saucepan.
Boil over medium heat to soft ball stage (soft ball is formed by dropping 1/2 teaspoon of mixture into a cup of cold water).
Add dates and continue cooking to soft ball stage again.
Cool slightly and add chopped nuts.
Turn onto buttered pan or platter; knead until creamy and stiff.
Form into 4 or more rolls.
Wrap rolls and place in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad delight
directions: Serve on lettuce topped with salad dressing thinned with a little cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in bowl.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in zucchini and walnuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 30 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, and vanilla together until it is smooth. Add in the salt, baking soda and sour milk. Stir that well. Add flour in one cup at a time mixing after each addition. Mix bananas in. Fill pans about 3/4 full of the dough. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with the skin on and cool.
Peel potatoes and cut into small pieces.
Dice the onion and green pepper and add to potatoes.
Add the salad olives and chopped eggs and stir in salad dressing.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; grease and flour a tube pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Tube pan is best.)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cocoa lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat baking sheets; set aside.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and corn syrup and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients until blended. Drop mixture by spoonfuls 3 inches apart on baking sheets.
Bake 9 minutes or until cookies are spread thin and are deep brown, but still soft.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheets.
Work quickly with spatula, removing cookies to cool completely on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: roast beef in cooking bag
directions: Combine ingredients.
Trim fat from beef roast.
Combine all in cooking bag and cook at 350° until beef is done.
Makes its own gravy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate sharp and mild Cheddar cheeses; set at room temperature until soft.
To cream cheese, add the Tabasco, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce; mix.
Combine mild and sharp cheeses with cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Shape into 2 large balls.
Crush pecans and parsley flakes; roll cheese balls in this mixture until coated.

title: french-style peas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion, lettuce and mushrooms. Saute until onion is transparent.
Add peas and water.
Cook over medium heat, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: southern style hominy
directions: You will also need 1 cloth sack and large wash pot.
A wooden frame with 1/4-inch spacing wire (hardware cloth) bottom will be useful for washing husk from corn if you are making this size batch.
Smaller batches can be cleaned by hand.

title: winford's secret barbecue sauce
directions: Grind up onions, bell pepper and celery in food processor or grinder.
Cook bacon to be crispy.
Crumble bacon and add to onions, bell pepper and celery along with bacon grease.
Cook to a mush.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and Cattleman's barbecue sauce. Add cornstarch to thicken and salt and pepper to taste.

title: dill pickles
directions: Stir sugar and vinegar through cut up pickles, making sure all sugar is wet.
Add pickling spice and let sit, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let soak good in the syrup.
Add to jar.

title: suzy's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, add oil, beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, spices and salt.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternating with nuts, zucchini and drained pineapple.
Bake 1 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Great on Wheat Thins!

title: pistachio bread
directions: Combine
all ingredients
and
mix
with
a
spoon
(no mixer).
Grease 2 loaf pans and dust with a mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar
and cinnamon to taste.
Any leftover can be used to sprinkle on top of loaves.	Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
When cool,
wrap
in
foil and refrigerate overnight. This enhances the flavor. Freezes well.

title: creamed chicken a la king
directions: Saute diced chicken breast and onion until chicken is cooked. Add canned soups and a little milk to thin slightly.
Add peas and carrots to suit your taste.
Prepare puff pastry shells.
Serve. (Can also be served over egg noodles or rice.)

title: baked potato fluff
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Mix in with mashed potatoes, onion, cheese, eggs and flour.
Put in greased casserole dish. Top with canned onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Put into bowl in layers the following:
lettuce, pepper, celery, onion, green peas (drained), mayonnaise and sugar.
Cover top with cheese and sprinkle top with bacon bits.
Cover with plastic wrap and let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: valerie's best brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). In medium mixing bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup melted butter; stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Stir in nuts, if desired, and chocolate chunks.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan; cut into squares.
Makes about 36 brownies.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs; beat well after each one.
Add sweet potatoes; mix well. Sift together rest of dry ingredients.
Mix well and bake in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with Caramel Icing.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut avocados in half and remove pits.
Spoon out and mash pulp.
Blend in remaining ingredients, mixing until smooth. Makes 2 cups dip.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except macaroni, cheese and mushroom soup and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken delight
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix cream of chicken soup, butter and salad dressing together.
After ingredients are well mixed, spread a small amount of mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken and spread remaining mixture over chicken.	Sprinkle potato chips over chicken, then sprinkle almond chips over potato chips.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until chicken is tender.
You may also microwave this dish with lid or plastic wrap for 25 minutes or until chicken is done all the way through.
Best served with potatoes with onions, green beans and garlic bread.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter until smooth and creamy.
In large bowl, pour chocolate mixture over Chex and mix until well coated.
Let cool 20 to 30 minutes.
Transfer mixture to brown grocery bag and add powdered sugar.
Fold bag over and shake until well coated with powdered sugar.
Add more sugar, if needed, when mix is completely cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Put onions and peppers through food chopper.
Mix, then cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar to peppers and onions.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal while hot.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over lard.
Add and mix the flour, baking powder and salt.
Store in refrigerator until you are ready to use it.

title: creamy oyster broccoli stew
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan; combine milk and soup.
Stir in broccoli, potatoes and onion.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until bubbly, breaking up broccoli with fork until thawed.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool. Cover and chill.
At serving time, in 3-quart saucepan, reheat soup.
In saucepan, place the fresh undrained oysters; cook over medium heat until edges curl.
Add to broccoli mixture; heat through.
If using canned oysters, just add undrained oysters directly to soup; heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ten dollar fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a large pan or baking dish.
Combine milk, flour, sugar and baking powder.
Pour over melted butter. Pour cooked hot fruit in center of batter.
Spread a little.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, maybe a little longer.

title: cumin rice
directions: Bring consomme to boil; add cumin.
In skillet saute vegetables in butter until soft.
Add rice and saute until golden brown.
Put in a large casserole.
Pour boiling liquid over rice. Cover and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Stir and check for doneness of rice.

title: yakitori(japanese skewered chicken)
directions: Combine sake (sherry), soy sauce and sugar in medium saucepan. Pare the ginger and cut into paper thin slices; add to saucepan. Bring to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer 15 minutes, or until sauce is reduced to 1 1/4 cups.
Preheat broiler or hibachi.
Dip skewered chicken pieces into sauce.
Broil 2 minutes.
Brush again with sauce and serve garnished with watercress.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Beat well. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together; add to melted butter and milk mixture.
Bring these ingredients to a boil; boil hard for 2 minutes.
Add oats, peanut butter, vanilla and salt; blend well. Remove from stove and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper while mixture is still warm.
It takes about 1/2 hour for cookies to harden.

title: double chocolate mint dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth (first 5 ingredients).
Pour into prepared pan; bake 25 minutes. Cool completely in pan.
Spread Mint Cream Layer over cake (see following); chill.
Pour Chocolate Topping over dessert (see following).
Cover; chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix corn meal mix, flour and sugar thoroughly.
Add onion, mixing well. Stir in egg and milk.
Let batter rest for 10 minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls into 375° deep fat.
When done, they will float.
Drain on brown paper.

title: squash pickles
directions: Pack squash and onions in 1/2 cup salt and ice for 3 hours. Wash and drain good.
Boil remaining ingredients.
Add squash and onions and bring to another boil.
Put in pint jars and seal.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, heavy cream and half and half.
Beat well. Add milk.
Cook rice; add to egg mixture.

title: children's play dough
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Mix water, oil and coloring. Mix all together; knead dough, then play with it.
This is not edible.
Store in airtight bag or bowl.
Makes enough for 2 children.
Try with cookie cutters and rolling pin for fun.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Pour in an 8 or 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie pan, 1 1/2-inches apart.
Preheat oven to 325°. Bake 15 to 17 minutes.

title: hot chicken cheese
directions: Pre cook vegetables 5 minutes (may use fresh or frozen).
Put chicken breasts on bottom of 9x13 baking dish.
Put cooked vegetables on top; salt & pepper.
Add soup and spread over top. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: sweet chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray nonstick spray in casserole dish. Place half of soup mix on bottom of dish with 2 tablespoons of water and mix.
Place chops in dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar on chops (enough sugar to cover each chop).
Pour the rest of mushroom soup over chops.
Slice onion over chops.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container and sample taste for sweetness. Add choice of fruit to mixture to bring it up to fill line on freezer. This makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In large saucepan, melt peanut butter, 1 cup condensed milk and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in peanuts.
Spread mixture in wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate morsels, remaining condensed milk and butter.
Spread chocolate mixture on top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off wax paper and cut.
Tightly cover leftovers.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix all together.
Place into pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: Cut each individual biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag or bowl.
Piece by piece, roll biscuit pieces into sugar mixture and place in a Bundt pan.
Melt margarine in cup and stir in leftover sugar mixture.
Pour over biscuit pieces in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Pour over sliced tomatoes. Marinate 30+ minutes. Serve on chilled plate.

title: shanghai casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic powders in a lightly greased skillet.
Add celery, vegetables and soup.
Stir in rice and seasonings.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sour cream
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and beat well.
This makes a sour cream that can be used in any recipe calling for sour cream.

title: pea salad
directions: After you put everything in a bowl, then you pour ranch dressing over the top and mix together, then put in refrigerator until thickens.

title: strawberry cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill until firm.
Looks nice in a jello mold topped with fresh mint leaves.

title: noodles in white sauce
directions: Cook noodles per package directions.
Drain and set aside.

title: white chocolate macadamia bark
directions: Grease bottom of 8-inch square pan; line bottom with sheet of wax paper.
Heat dry 10-inch skillet over medium heat, add Macadamias.
Toast 5 to 6 minutes, stir occasionally, until golden.
Remove from skillet; cool.
Return skillet to heat, repeat toasting procedure with coconut.
Stir white chocolate chips in medium-size heavy saucepan over very low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in toasted Macadamias. Spread chocolate mixture evenly in prepared pan, sprinkle with coconut, pressing in gently.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes, until set.
Remove bark from pan and peel off wax paper.
Break bark into irregular pieces.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Makes 3/4 pound.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients.
Press dough in a 12-inch pizza pan, forming a rim along the edge.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.
Cool and cut.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cover potatoes with water and add salt.
Simmer potatoes for about 25 minutes until cooked.
Dice potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix potatoes with garlic, onions, salt, sour cream and cottage cheese. Fold into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake for about 35 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: taboli wheat salad(lebanese)
directions: Chop parsley and onions; add tomato.
Wash cracked wheat and soak in water approximately 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss and serve.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Mix dressing, wine, garlic, onion and seasonings.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Drain.
Place chicken on grill (medium) or rack of broiler pan. Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes on each side.

title: broccoli with orange sauce
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. In a saucepan, melt butter. Whisk in cornstarch until smooth. Gradually stir in orange juice and zest. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened. Drain broccoli and drizzle with sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashion brownies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, chocolate and nuts.
Bake in a moderate oven about 25 minutes, until it pulls away from edges of pan.

title: lemon spinach salad
directions: Mix jello, water, mayonnaise and vinegar together and heat until dissolved.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Drain frozen spinach and squeeze out moisture.
Add spinach, cottage cheese, celery and onion to jello mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: baska (easter bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water to which salt and 1 teaspoon sugar has been added.
Melt butter.
Add potato water, 1 cup sugar and egg yolks.
Mix and then add yeast mixture plus cream, ground anise (or anise flavoring), raisins and unsifted flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise.
Work down 3 times.

title: caramel corn
directions: When having to make biscuits in a hurry, add 1 teaspoon baking powder to 2 cups biscuit mix.
Also, if making waffles or pancakes, add 1 teaspoon baking powder

title: cranberry apple salad
directions: Heat and strain cranberry sauce, reserving liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in water; add salt, lemon juice and reserved cranberry liquid.
Chill until partially firm; beat until fluffy.
Mix together mayonnaise, diced apples, cranberries and pecans.
Chill in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 18.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with melted sweet chocolate.

title: ralph's fruitcake
directions: Cream butter.
Add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Briefly beat in vanilla.
Toss together flour, salt and baking powder and beat into creamed mixture 1 cup at a time (and no more than that).
Mix until smooth after each addition.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Combine batter with fruit and nut mixture.
Turn into pans and bake at 275° for 60 to 75 minutes for small cakes, 2 1/2 to 3 hours for large.
When cool, start misting with bourbon.

title: uncle bob's chicken stir-fry(low-fat)
directions: In a pan sprayed with Pam, add all ingredients except sweet and sour sauce.
You can add a little water to the pan to help steam the vegetables.
When vegetables are almost done, add sweet and sour sauce.
Heat and serve over noodles or rice.

title: fresh orange cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add rind, shortening and eggs; beat.
Add liquid; beat thoroughly.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in buttered casserole.

title: potato casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, pepper, onion, salt and green peppers in greased baking dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over ingredients.
Can sprinkle top with grated cheese. Cover and cook at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: whole meal casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients, then add tomato paste, mushroom soup, water, chili powder and salt.
Cover and cook 30 minutes or until done.
Add corn, olives and cooked noodles.
Put in greased casserole; cover with grated cheese and bake until cheese melts. It is better to let it set a while before baking.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Layer ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until bubbly.
Delicious with ham or can be used as a dessert.

title: hot beef and bean dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Stir in refried beans, onion, 1 1/2 cups cheese and picante sauce.
Spread mixture into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt. Add eggs, beating well. Stir in corn and milk. Pour ingredients in buttered casserole and bake 1 hour at 400° or until golden brown and silver knife inserted comes out clean.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop fine, cabbage, onion, pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Chill in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Boil fryers with salt and pepper to taste until tender.
Cool and remove from bone.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: candy apples
directions: You will need 10 sticks.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place cooked chicken in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix Ritz cracker crumbs, butter and poppy seed together. Sprinkle over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry tapioca salad
directions: Cook 1 cup tapioca, pinch of salt and 5 cups boiling water for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Take off heat and add one package of raspberry Jell-O, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water.
Mix well.
Put in bowl and set in refrigerator.
Stir often until set.
Next day, add frozen raspberries and Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Boil noodles as directed.
While noodles are cooking mix the following ingredients to form the meatballs:
salt, egg, hamburger, crackers and onion flakes.
Drop by teaspoonful into warm electric skillet (250 degrees).
When meatballs are done drain off grease if necessary.
To make the sauce combine the following ingredients: mustard, catsup, brown sugar, water and chili powder.
When noodles are done, drain and put them in the skillet with the meatballs and then add the sauce mixture.
Simmer until heated thoroughly.

title: aunt theresa's butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar and milk. Cook this mixture until thick and brown. The darker it is, the more butterscotch taste it has. Mix milk and flour together. Add egg yolk and mix. Stir this mixture into the first mixture, stirring constantly. Cook until thick and pour into baked pie crust. Makes 1 pie.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients (vegetables and turkey) together.
Add gravy to moisten.
Put into pie shell.
Carefully take second pie shell out of tin and place over shell with mixture.

title: salad
directions: Mix mayo and sugar together.
Add all ingredients, except cheese and bacon bits.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.

title: freezer pickles
directions: In large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients.
Cover with water and let stand for 2 hours.
Then drain and add sugar and vinegar. Refrigerate for 2 days.
Transfer to freezer containers and place in freezer.
Thaw as needed.
Serve and enjoy!!

title: party chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with salad dressing to hold together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve the gelatin in hot cranberry juice.
Cool until partially set.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate.

title: swiss turkey quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In medium bowl, toss cheese with flour and bouillon; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set, topping with French fried onions during last 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease deep 10-inch pie plate. Cook broccoli and/or cauliflower to tender crisp in salt water, about 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix with onion, green pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed, or 1 minute with hand beater. Pour over contents in pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients. Fold into pumpkin.
Spread into a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up and cool in refrigerator.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut the tops off peppers.
Dice the onion.
Mix ground beef, onion, rice, crushed tomatoes, salt and pepper in bowl until thoroughly combined.
Stuff into peppers.
Place peppers in a large pot; fill pot with tomato puree and water, just enough to cover peppers.
Stir occasionally.
Cook for 1 hour or until you can pierce a pepper with a fork.
The peppers will be tender when done.

title: batter-dipped hot dogs
directions: Combine corn meal mix and pepper.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Insert wooden skewer in one end of each hot dog.
Coat with additional flour; dip into corn meal batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Drain on absorbant paper.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy-cheesy lasagna
directions: Combine sauce, bay leaves, oregano and garlic powder in Dutch oven; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour, stirring often.

title: christmas toffee
directions: Butter a cookie sheet. Melt butter in 2 qt. sauce pan, stir in sugar gradually. Add syrup and water. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally until a little bit in cold water becomes very brittle.

title: cool and easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved.
Add enough ice to cold water to measure 1 cup.
Add to gelatin; stir until ice is melted.
Add whipped topping; stir with wire whisk until well blended. Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is very thick and will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and condensed milk.
Mix well.
Add lime juice and blend well.
Beat one of the egg whites until firm. Fold into mixture.
Turn into pie shell.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon, about 20 minutes or until desired thickness.
Makes about 1 pint jar.

title: italian hot dish
directions: Brown together the first five ingredients.
Add the soup and water to the noodles in a two-quart baking dish.
Stir in the browned ingredients.
Scatter the cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together and make 14 cakes; dip in egg and bread crumbs. Fry in deep fat after the cakes have been in the refrigerator for several hours so they can set and not fall apart when fried.

title: strawberry pie (fresh)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and strawberry jello; bring to boil and let boil for no more than 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Wash and slice strawberries and put in pie shell.
Pour cooled jello mixture over berries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: thin brownies
directions: Melt chocolate, Crisco and salt.
Add sugar and blend. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and 1/2 of the nuts. Spread on cookie sheet 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over potatoes and mix.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart serving dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Spread on top 2 cups cornflakes, crushed and mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dayspringer(drink)
directions: Combine ingredients in blender. Run on high until smooth and well blended.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery and brown ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients except Chinese noodles.
Turn into 2 1/2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Remove and cover with Chinese noodles; bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
This can be made a day ahead.
Also freezes well.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Stir in ice cream until smooth.
Pour into serving bowl.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip, fruit and nuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: micro-fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in large bowl.
Add milk and margarine; do not stir.
Put in microwave for 3 minutes on 80% until butter is soft and melted.
Mix together.
Put in buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: marinated three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine all vegetables in large bowl.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables; mix well.
Cover; chill overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 one-cup servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips. Spoon into 6 ungreased 1-cup baking dishes. Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
In small bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt morsels and butter; stir until smooth.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
Stir in brown sugar; cool 5 minutes.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture. Stir in nuts.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Makes 35 brownies.

title: sweet beet pickles
directions: Cover cooked, peeled beets with mixture of other ingredients. Let all come to boiling point.
Pack in jars and seal while hot.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix and pie filling.
Spread in oblong pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: carol's corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 2 1/2-quart baking dish with a portion of the butter.
Mix in blender on high speed all ingredients if using whole corn.
Pour into baking dish.

title: cheese spread(instead of a grilled cheese, try this spreadable cheese recipe.)
directions: In a bowl, mix cocoa and sugar to a paste with cold water. Add to saucepan of boiling water; stir.
Add syrup and salt; cook at least 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.

title: plum dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes and rice them.
Add eggs, salt and baking powder.
Add flour until dough does not stick.
Take some dough; roll in hands to form a snake.
Lay plums on top of this; cut dough between plums and roll dough around plums.
Drop into boiling salt water until plum is soft.
Take out of water; roll in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Eat warm.

title: lemon supreme
directions: Mix all together, cook at 350 degrees for about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Saut onion and green pepper in fat until onions are yellow.
Add meat and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 2 quart baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour removing cover last 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Put the peppers in a pan with cold water to cover.
Bring slowly to a boil, then drain.
Cut off the tops of the peppers and scoop out the seeds.
Blend together the chopped onion, mushrooms, the cooked rice, salt and pepper.
Fill each pepper with this mixture and dot with butter.
Pour the tomato juice over the stuffed peppers.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Sear meat, onion and garlic until pink disappears in oleo. Add cornmeal and mix well.
Add 1 quart hot water, salt, pepper, comino seed and chili powder.
Simmer 1 hour in a large pot.
Add beans and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: hot chicken
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before baking.
Grate cheese over top.
Cover with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Blend all together. Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze. May substitute lemon-lime soda, grape, etc. for orange.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix well with fingers and roll into one-inch round balls. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 40 balls.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter and boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until it begins to thicken (3 minutes).
Drop on waxed paper by teaspoon and let cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, celery stick, bay leaves and onion.
When chicken is done, debone chicken and discard celery, bay leaves and onion.
Saute margarine, chopped pepper, celery and onions.
Add flour, 2 cups of the Velveeta cheese and chicken broth.
Cook mixture until thick.
Cook spaghetti in remaining chicken broth. Drain; add spaghetti to sauce.
Add deboned chicken.
Grate cheese over top and cook in oven until cheese melts.

title: rum chiffon cake
directions: Soften gelatin in water for 5 minutes.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, sugar and salt and beat.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture almost boils.
The mixture should coat the back of a spoon, then add the gelatin.
Stir to dissolve. Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into custard with rum.
Turn into a baked pie shell. Cover with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.
Chill.

title: soft spray
directions: Mix in spray bottle.
Keeps ticks off animals and people.

title: seafood primavera
directions: Combine ReaLemon brand, cornstarch and salt; mix well.
Add scallops and shrimp.

Cover; marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes. In large skillet, over high heat, cook and stir mushrooms, carrots, garlic and thyme in margarine until tender-crisp, about 8 minutes. Add seafood mixture; cook and stir 5 to 8 minutes until seafood is opaque.
Add pea pods, onions and sherry (if desired); heat through.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana pineapple shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container.
Blend at low speed 15 to 20 seconds to mix.
Blend at high speed 30 to 60 seconds, turning on and off frequently, until well blended. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: oatmeal pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine oats and milk and allow to stand for 5 minutes, then stir in pumpkin, eggs and margarine.
In a separate bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and spices.
Gradually add dry ingredients to oatmeal mixture.
