Stir in raisins and nuts, mixing well.
Place in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes one loaf.

title: shrimp congealed salad
directions: Heat the undiluted soup and add and melt the cream cheese. When the cream cheese is blended, add the gelatin and stir well. Cool.
Add the onion, pepper, celery, mayonnaise and shrimp.
Pour into a mold if desired or into a square or oblong dish. Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in stew pot until tender.
Cool, bone and skin. Cut into bite-size pieces.
Arrange chips in bottom of greased cake pan.
Put on chicken.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel, then spread on chicken.
Shred cheese and sprinkle on top.
Cook in 350° oven for 30
minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir peanut butter, honey and butter together until well mixed.
Mix in wheat germ and nonfat dry milk.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Chill and eat.
Makes 18 to 20.

title: ground turkey sausage
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape into patties and fry in oil on medium heat.
Do not overcook.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream butter and shortening with sugar and vanilla. Add egg.
Cream until mixture is fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten batter with bottom of a water glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots for 20 minutes, or until slightly tender.

title: breaded herbed fish fillets(catfish or trout)
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Coat fillets with cooking spray. Dredge in bread crumb mixture. Place fillets on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Use for dipping vegetables in.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything.
Be sure potatoes are separated.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Top with Durkee French fried onions and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: working girl spoon rolls
directions: *One and one-half sticks margarine may be substituted for oil.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine soups, broth and Ro-Tel tomatoes; blend until smooth. Place in casserole dish: layer of chicken, layer of tortillas, onion, cheese and soup and tomato mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for one hour.
Serves 6.

title: creamy mostaccioli with snap peas
directions: Cook pasta, adding snap peas last 1 minute.
Drain.
Warm sauce and pork, add water if too thick.
Add to pasta and peas; add tomato and toss.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: bread dip
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Cut the top off a round loaf of bread and hollow out loaf of bread.
Cut the bread taken out of loaf into cubes.
Brush cubes with 2 tablespoons vegetable oil and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Pour cheese mixture in loaf of bread, then wrap tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: gazebo cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add onions, celery and carrots; saute until soft.
Add chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add potato soup, cheese, parsley, hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add sherry and stir.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 cups.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a saucepan, bring to rolling boil stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes, over medium heat. Stir in chocolate until melted, add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Pour into greased pan. Makes 3 lbs.

title: easy homemade strawberry ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over sausages in crock-pot.
Cook on low heat for 6 hours.
(You adjust the amount of each ingredient based on the amount of cocktail sausages used.)

title: western dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake to mix well.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Makes one pint.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, drain and season well with salt and pepper.
Pour Ranch style dressing over; mix and serve.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oleo and cheese.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs. Beat.
Add flour and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 65 minutes in 325° oven.
No preheating.

title: cheese (like velveeta)
directions: Let milk sour until thick; when thickened, scald until it is too hot to touch.
Pour into cheesecloth and let hang to dry overnight or 12 hours.
Crumble curds to make fine crumbs.
Mix in soda and let stand 2 hours.
Place into a large skillet (preferably stainless steel) and add butter.
Melt butter with curds then add cream and salt.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Pour in buttered container and let stand until completely cooled.
Slice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and cream cheese. Alternate flour and eggs (1 cup flour/2 eggs). Add vanilla and rum.

title: coke  - cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from fruits, heat and pour over gelatin to dissolve. Cool. Add cokes. Cut cherries in half. Add cherries and pineapples to gelatin mixture.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together; mixture will be soft.
Make into balls.
Freeze to make solid.
Put in 13 x 9 pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
When done, pour sauce over them.

title: butter rolls
directions: Roll each biscuit until thin.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 pats margarine and a little cinnamon to each biscuit.
Roll up and pinch ends.
Put in single layer.
Sprinkle sugar on top (about 1/2 cup for 5 biscuits) and a little cinnamon.
Pour milk to just cover biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done.
Baste with juice while cooking.
Juice will be just a little thick.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 1 loaf pan.
Combine flour, soda and sugar in medium mixing bowl.
In another bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add oil and almond extract to eggs.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture and stir well.
Fold berries into batter. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
While cake is cooking, mix milk, sugar and 1 package of coconut.
Punch holes in cake after cake has cooked.
Pour mixture over cake while hot.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: dry gelatin salad
directions: You will need 1 felt tip, 1 (3-inch) sharp paring knife, 1 cast metal ice cream scoop, 1 (8-inch) butcher knife, 2 to 3 large bowls and 1 (2 to 3 gallon) kettle bowl.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut green peppers into chunks, combine with sliced onions & cucumbers, add garlic and salt (this can be put in clean sink). Cover with ice then cover with a towel and let set at least 3 hours (overnight is best).
Drain well, place in large pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in sauce pan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour mixture over cucumber mix.
Heat to a boil & seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on greased cookie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: sausage and cornbread pie
directions: Cook sausage,
onion
and
garlic
until meat is brown. Stir in	crumbled meat that has been drained and add tomatoes, chiles, corn
and chili powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Spoon mixture into a greased baking dish and set aside.

title: chicken - sausage casserole
directions: Mix sausage, rice, soup and mushrooms.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with chicken pieces and then top with remaining rice mixture.
Cover with buttered crumbs or croutons.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the milk, sugar and butter.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Syrup should form a soft ball stage when tested in cold water, 232°.)
Remove from heat and stir in the chips and creme.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread into a greased 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Chill until firm.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and celery in a large skillet. Cook until meat is done and browned.
Drain off pan drippings. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over hamburger buns.

title: cookies on a stick
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix on medium speed the sugar, brown sugar and butter until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture until blended.
By hand stir in peanuts and corn flakes until coated.

title: taco pie i
directions: Cook ground beef with onion; drain grease.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick for 1 minute.
Pour over chilies.
Bake 25 minutes at 450°.
Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: beef stew meat
directions: Using the broth, cook the celery, carrots and onion for approximately 15 minutes, then add the potatoes and beef and cook until done.
Then add the Prego and let simmer.

title: berry or apple crisp topping
directions: Combine until crumbly.
For fruit, add and mix 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Sprinkle topping over fruit mixture. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
This recipe is for an 8 x 8-inch pan.
If you use a 9 x 13-inch pan, use 1 1/2 times the topping recipe.

title: k-bars
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, butter, white syrup and peanut butter.
Put in microwave on High until mixture comes to a boil, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well and put in 9 x 13 pan lightly sprayed with Pam. Frost with chocolate chips and butterscotch chips melted together.

title: dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion (you may use 1 cup each).
Combine both kinds of bread crumbs, onion, celery, seasonings and butter.
Add egg and mix lightly.
Heat enough chicken stock to moisten crumbs and pour over dressing.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add margarine and milk; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 90 seconds, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix for one minute.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm.

title: taco salad]
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion until onion is clear.
Drain and rinse well.

title: fried country ham and red-eye gravy
directions: Slice ham 1/4-inch thick.
Trim off skin and part of the fat. (Save trimmings for seasoning beans and vegetables and for making red-eye gravy.)
Place a little of the saved fat in a medium-hot skillet.
After fat has heated, place sliced ham in the skillet and let cook for 2 minutes per side.
If ham is overcooked, it becomes tough and hard.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice squash into 1/2 -inch slices, parboil for 3 minutes.
To make filling, combine remaining ingredients, except crumbs and margarine.	Mix well.
Place squash in baking dish, alternating with filling.
Top with bread crumbs and dabs of margarine.
Bake in 375 degree oven for 35 minutes.	Serves 6-8.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites with baking powder until stiff at high speed, then add the vanilla extract and sugar and beat.
After beating this at high speed, add walnuts and Ritz crackers broken into large pieces.
Beat on medium until all is mixed thoroughly.
Pour mixture into buttered pie pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool and serve with fresh unsweetened whipped cream.
Also very good with ice cream.

title: split pea vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine peas, water, allspice, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir in potatoes, carrots, onions, ham and cabbage; return to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 5 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all together, adding Fritos last.
Serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
This can be doubled and cooked in a 9 x 13-inch pan for a large crowd.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Cream butter and sugars until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, then milk, alternating with flour.
Add vanilla, oatmeal, raisins and peanut butter. Drop by the teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts together.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: refrigerated slaw
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage, onion and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Simmer until well blended.
Pour boiling liquid over cabbage mixture.
Cover and let set for about 3 hours.
Stir.
Let set 2 or 3 hours.
Refrigerate. Will keep for 5 or 6 weeks if refrigerated.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice; chop onions and peppers.
Let stand for 3 hours with salt over them; drain.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and spices.
Bring to boil; add cucumbers.
Heat thoroughly, but don't boil.
Pack while hot.

title: beef taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.
Cook beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning and pour into pie pan.
Sprinkle with chiles.
In another bowl, beat with hand mixer the milk, biscuit mix and eggs for 1 minute until smooth. Pour over beef mixture and bake 25 minutes.
Remove and top with diced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for several hours.

title: mexican sauce
directions: Cook onion in butter until softened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer five minutes.
Spoon out cloves and discard.
Brush sauce over ham steak as they grill (or any meat).

title: christmas bread
directions: Cool scalded milk to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and 1 tablespoons sugar.
To the milk add 1 cup sugar, yeast mixture and half the flour.
Beat well.
Add butter, fruit, cardamom, almonds, salt, eggs and remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Knead.
Cover and let rise to double.
Punch down and form two loaves.
Let rise.
When double, bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: meatball appetizers
directions: Mix together like a meat loaf the hamburger, egg, onion and salt.
Shape
into	small meatballs.
Combine jelly, chili sauce and
lemon juice; cook until jelly dissolves.
Pour over meatballs (raw).
Bake in oven 1 hour at 225°.
These can also be done in a crock-pot.

title: snappy carrots
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of salted water until tender. Drain and place carrots in a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Stir into carrots.
Mix crushed crackers with butter.
Sprinkle on carrots.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
This may be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream shortening, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat with mixer until mixture is very light and creamy.
Add flour and buttermilk and beat 2 more minutes. In small mixing bowl, mix cocoa, soda and hot water.
Add to rest of batter.
Put into 3 (8-inch) round pans or 1 (9 x 12 x 2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken apricot
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish, skin side down.
Combine rest of ingredients and spread half of sauce on chicken.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Turn chicken over and add rest of sauce. Continue baking 50 to 60 minutes, or until done.
Can be frozen or prepared in advance.
Serves 4.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan the cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle (dry) yellow cake mix over top. Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Melt margarine and pour over top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cold topped with whipped cream, Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: amaretto creamer for coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, use 2 tablespoons creamer in 6 ounces of hot coffee. Great for holiday gifts!

title: easy chili
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in a Dutch oven; cook until beef is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain off pan drippings. Add remaining ingredients, except kidney beans; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in beans; continue to cook, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and cook an additional 15 minutes.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add shortening and blend until crumbly. Add water.
If possible allow to chill or use ice water.
Roll on floured board.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: chocolate heath bar cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake as directed.
After cake is baked, poke holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over top of cake.
Let it seep into cake.
Warm fudge topping slightly and pour over cake. Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: rich lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: frosted date balls
directions: Combine flour and salt; sift twice.
Cream the butter and gradually add sugar.
Add milk and vanilla; stir in the sifted flour.
Blend in dates and nuts.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Place about 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 300° oven about 20 minutes, until light brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine first 7 ingredients, beat 2 minutes on medium speed; pour into greased pie plate or pan.
Place drained peaches over batter. Combine cream cheese, sugar and juice; beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Spoon over prepared pan within 1 inch of edge of pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top and bake 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Filling will appear soft.
Store in refrigerator.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Add sugar, salt and spices to squash and mix well.
Beat eggs with milk, then mix with squash.
Pour in pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place cooked broccoli into buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, water, mayonnaise and lemon juice together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle almonds on top of soup mixture and top with cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Fry bacon while potatoes are boiling.
Set bacon aside to cool.
Drain potatoes.
Put 1/2 of the potatoes into a casserole dish.
Put 1/2 cheese, salt, and pepper on top.
Make another layer.
Crumble bacon on top.
Pour melted butter over everything. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring the syrup and sugar to a boil in a saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and cereal.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper and cool.

title: chicken breast a la mary
directions: Cook chicken breasts for 30 minutes.
In water with celery, onion, salt, carrots and chicken bouillon cube.
Cool.

title: potato chip cookies(taste like pecan sandies.)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in chips and nuts.

title: mary's creamy baked cheesecake
directions: You will need a 10-inch spring-form cake pan, three inches deep.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into 1 cup measuring cup.
Drain mandarin orange juice into same cup so you have 1 cup of liquid.
Throw away rest of liquid.
Mix 1 cup juice with dry pudding and stir well. In bowl, mix canned fruit and banana, cut into bite size pieces. Add glaze to bowl and mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: egg drops
directions: Mix flour, egg, milk and salt; beat well.
Pour slowly by small spoonfuls into boiling soup.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Use in any soup.

title: pumpkin trifle
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup cake crumbs for top.
Divide remaining crumbs into four portions; sprinkle one portion into the bottom of a trifle bowl or 3-quart serving bowl.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, spices, milk and pudding mix; mix until smooth. Spoon half into the serving bowl.
Sprinkle with a second portion of crumbs.
Whip cream until stiff; spoon half into bowl. Sprinkle with a third portion of crumbs.
Top with remaining pumpkin mixture, then last portion of crumbs and remaining whipped cream.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top, around edge of bowl. Place cherries in center if desired.
Cover and chill 2 hours before serving.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: "fruit dip"
directions: Mix together and serve with variety of fruits.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together the cheeses and the seasoning mix.
Spread on large cookie sheet or round pizza pan.
Then pour taco sauce over top.
Layer with toppings of your choice.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend in wet ingredients until slightly moistened.
Place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and stir in butter. Mix other ingredients into the beans and pour all into a casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with onion rings and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Chop olives; combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight for full flavor.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread dip in shallow baking dish and bake 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-cherry squares
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into 9-inch square pan.
Chill.
Stir chocolate and water over low heat until smooth. Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in chocolate.
Fold in 2 cups of the Cool Whip.
Spread over crumbs.
Top with cherry filling. Chill and garnish with remaining topping.
Makes 9 servings.

title: baked chicken in wine sauce
directions: Cook chicken and drain.
Brown chicken in butter and put in baking dish.
To the drippings in skillet add onions and saute until tender.
Add all other ingredients and cook 1 minute.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate sandwich gobs
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and beaten eggs in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture alternately with milk, until combined.
Drop spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove to cooling rack.
Form sandwiches by putting icing between 2 cookies.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, covered with foil.

title: lemon pudding cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix crushed wafers, 1 tablespoon of sugar and melted butter. Press firmly into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: molded creamy orange salad
directions: Mix gelatin, orange juice concentrate and hot water; add sherbet, ginger ale and oranges.
Pour into Jell-O mold and chill until set.

title: granny's fried apples
directions: Wash, peel, core and quarter apples.
Place in large heavy skillet with a little water and cook apples until slightly tender. Add sugar and oleo and cook until right consistency, being careful not to burn.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour. Measure. Add baking powder, soda and salt and sift again. Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy. Add well beaten eggs and mix thoroughly. Add vanilla and dry ingredients alternately with milk and mashed bananas, stirring only enough after each addition to blend thoroughly. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add the dry ingredients and vanilla.
Fold in the apples and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top, or serve with ice cream.

title: easy mushroom rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine rice, onion soup, beef broth, mushrooms and butter in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Bake for 60 minutes.

title: tofu mushroom loaf
directions: Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms in oil.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Add the onion-mushroom mixture to the tofu mixture.
Fold gently and spoon into oiled loaf pan.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Resift twice with soda and set aside. Cream butter and add sugar slowly, beating constantly to cream well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in dairy sour cream.
Add flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well and constantly.
Stir in lemon extract and turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Use salt free shortening or fat for greasing pan.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for about 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Place pan on rack to cool 5 minutes.
Loosen cake around edge of pan and edge of tube with dull side of knife.
Press toward pan, rather than toward cake.
This protects crust.
Turn cake onto rack to cool completely.
Serve plain.
When freezing this cake, either whole or cut, wrap in several thickness of clear plastic or aluminum foil.

title: swiss vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw and drain the frozen vegetables.
Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and 1 cup onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Top with cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes, or until onions are golden brown.

title: quick hot rolls
directions: Crumble yeast cake in a cup and fill with milk.
Put shortening in saucepan and melt.
Add water, then the milk and yeast.
(Don't have shortening and water too warm.) Mix with dry ingredients and let stand.
When double in bulk, work down and cut into rolls.
Let rise.

title: fried zucchini(serves 4)
directions: In a colander, toss zucchini with salt.
Let drain for 15 minutes.
Pat dry.
In a bowl, whisk together eggs and mustard. Dip zucchini slices in flour, then egg mixture, then bread crumbs. Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain on paper towels.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crumble sausage into a large skillet. Cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, breaking up clumps, until cooked through and lightly browned.
Remove from skillet and drain.
Spoon into 10-inch pie pan. Top with hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and pepper.
Pour over hash browns and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until slightly puffed and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: breakfast change
directions: Fill soup bowl 3/4 full with water.
Place 2 ounces thin filet of salmon in the water; let it sink to the bottom.
Break an egg into the water to rest over the salmon.
Cover with Saran Wrap and place in microwave on High.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes or until egg white coagulates.
Remove with slotted spoon by inserting it under the salmon.
Remove from water with egg on top of salmon.
Place on rye toast.
Add dash of paprika.

title: homemade ice cream(for four-quart freezer)
directions: Scald milk until bubbles form around edge.
Remove from heat. Add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in half and half, vanilla and whipping cream.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes or longer.

title: chocolate mint squares
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Then add other ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: mushroom stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in the margarine or butter.
Drain and and retain margarine for later.
(Note - Cherie's Gourmet Tip: Microwave may be used to saute the onion and celery.)

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, pour off excess fat.
Place a layer of ground beef, layer of potatoes, layer of onion, carrot and peas in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers until ingredients are used up.
Pour can of chicken soup on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Mix well with hands.
Divide into thirds.
Make into rolls. Wrap and chill.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Mix all gently until blended.
Put into a 2-quart dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
I've made this so often that I believe I did invent it!

title: terrine of turkey
directions: Place the turkey in a large bowl.
Add the onion, parsley, garlic, bread crumbs, water, tomato paste, mustard, tamari and thyme.
Mix the ingredients together, then add the eggs and mix again until well combined.
Press the turkey mixture into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover the terrine with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove from oven and let cool for 1 hour.

Place another 9 x 5-inch loaf pan on top of the terrine and fill with dried beans or other heavy material such as a can of food, or cover with foil and top with something heavy. Refrigerate 2 to 3 days.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: After cooking broccoli (according to package) omitting salt, place in a baking dish.
Combine soup and cheese.
Add milk, mayonnaise and egg to soup mixture.
Pour over broccoli and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crumbs are lightly brown.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Early in day or day ahead: In large bowl, combine shortening, salt, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup butter or margarine (1 stick). Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture; stir until blended. In a small bowl, sprinkle yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar over 1/2 cup warm water (105° to 115°). Stir to mix slightly. Let rest 5 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling water (salted) for 5 minutes; drained.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Form into balls and dip in a mixture of chocolate chips and paraffin.
Set on wax paper; refrigerate.

title: cherry apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: speedy orange rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl and let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth (about 2 minutes).
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Roll dough into a 14 x 7-inch rectangle; spread with 1/2 of Orange Filling, leaving a 1 inch margin on long sides.
Roll jelly roll fashion, starting at long side.
Pinch seam.
Cut into 12 equal slices.
Place cut-side down in greased muffin pans. Cover and let rise in warm place, free from drafts, 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Spread remaining Orange Filling over tops of rolls.
Yield:
12 rolls.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer beans in baking dish.
Spread salsa over beans.
Layer sour cream over top.
Top with grated cheese.
Place in a 350° oven until cheese bubbles.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg and add milk, shortening and add all ingredients together.
Spoon dumplings on top of your broth.
Cook uncovered for 10 minutes and covered for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Add water; mix, then add cold milk.
Mix well.
Cook to desired thickness and serve over biscuits and butter.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pastry shell lined with 1/3 cup chopped pecans or 1/3 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put rice on bottom of roaster. Put chicken in and sprinkle with onion soup mix. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top. Bake about 2 hours at 350°. You may add green pepper and celery, if desired.

title: baked halibut
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Thaw frozen halibut.
Rinse and pat dry.
Place fish in greased baking pan.
Combine melted Crisco, olive oil, vinegar, lemon juice, salt, mustard, marjoram, garlic powder and pepper.
Drizzle over fish.
Bake at 450° for 18 minutes.
You may add vegetables the last 5 minutes.
Garnish with dill weed or lemon wedges.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the lime juice, water and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add nectarines and banana; toss to coat. In a 2 1/2-quart glass bowl, combine remaining fruits. Add nectarine mixture; stir gently. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving with a slotted spoon.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Stretch dough 12 x 18-inches.
Top with all ingredients and roll up lengthwise.
Pinch and tuck ends.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise 1 hour.
Slit top to allow steam to escape. Brush with olive oil.
Bake in preheated oven 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: orange delight cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and rind.
Beat until smooth.
Add sour milk and soda, then flour.
Drop from spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While hot, spread with 1 1/2 tablespoons orange juice and sugar to thin paste over cookies.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Slice apples into pie shell.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sift 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in margarine and sprinkle mix on top of apples.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and cook until apples are done and top is brown.
